36:28.870 --> 36:32.640
<b>我也是一时糊涂才告诉你 我知道你本来也会去咨询的</b><b>
I feel stupid telling you this. I'm sure you would have investigated.</b>

36:33.140 --> 36:36.510
<b>还他妈轮不到你来教我怎么做!</b><b>
I don't need you to tell me where the bear shit in the buckwheat.</b>

36:37.010 --> 36:40.110
<b>当然不 但你需要有人替你申请免税</b><b>
Of course not. But you do need someone to set it up for you.</b>

36:40.610 --> 36:41.880
<b>那会让你破费 比如 你得请个律师</b><b>
That'll cost you. A lawyer.</b>

36:42.380 --> 36:44.620
<b>那帮洗了卵蛋的杂碎?</b><b>
A bunch of ball-washing bastards!</b>

36:45.120 --> 36:48.290
<b>我想我可以替你办理 说不定能替你省点钱</b><b>
I suppose I could set it up for you. That would save you some money.</b>

36:48.790 --> 36:50.590
<b>你只要找来表格 剩下的事交给我</b><b>
You get the forms, I'll prepare them...</b>

36:51.090 --> 36:52.820
<b>用不着花什么钱</b><b>
nearly free of charge.</b>

36:54.060 --> 36:57.360
<b>我想要的也就是给我的同事每人三瓶啤酒而已</b><b>
I'd only ask three beers apiece for each of my coworkers.</b>

36:58.330 --> 36:59.850
<b>"同事?" 你当你发达了啊?</b><b>
"Coworkers." That's rich!</b>

37:00.700 --> 37:02.930
<b>在外面干活的时候要是能有瓶啤酒喝</b><b>
A man working outdoors feels more like a man...</b>

37:03.430 --> 37:06.840
<b>那才更像个爷们儿 这只是我的一点想法</b><b>
if he can have a bottle of suds. That's only my opinion...</b>

37:07.340 --> 37:08.330
<b>长官!</b><b>
sir.</b>

37:12.280 --> 37:13.910
<b>你们这群呆子看什么看? 干你们的活!</b><b>
What are you jimmies staring at?</b>

37:14.410 --> 37:16.000
<b>干活干活!</b><b>
Let's go! Work!</b>

37:25.520 --> 37:27.160
<b>就这样 在49年春天的一个早晨</b><b>
And that's how it came to pass...</b>

37:27.660 --> 37:30.030
<b>在完工头一天的上午十点</b><b>
that on the second-to-last day of the job...</b>

37:30.530 --> 37:34.800
<b>一群在车间屋顶铺沥青的囚犯</b><b>
the convict crew that tarred the factory roof in the spring of '49...</b>

37:35.300 --> 37:38.140
<b>在屋顶围坐在一起</b><b>
wound up sitting in a row at 10:00 in the morning...</b>

37:38.640 --> 37:41.310
<b>享受着清凉的啤酒 还有"殷勤"的服务</b><b>
drinking icy-cold beer, courtesy of the hardest screw...</b>

37:41.810 --> 37:47.280
<b>而且都是拜肖申克州立监狱有史以来最狠的狱吏所赐</b><b>
that ever walked a turn at Shawshank State Prison.</b>

37:47.780 --> 37:50.210
<b>趁凉喝 女士们</b><b>
Drink up while it's cold, ladies.</b>

37:51.320 --> 37:55.880
<b>那二球还摆出一副很大度的样子</b><b>
The colossal prick even managed to sound magnanimous.</b>

37:57.020 --> 38:01.360
<b>我们品味着啤酒 阳光洒满臂膀 恍如自由人</b><b>
We sat and drank with the sun on our shoulders and felt like free men.</b>

38:01.860 --> 38:05.000
<b>感觉是在修整自家的屋项</b><b>
We could have been tarring the roof of one of our own houses.</b>

38:05.500 --> 38:08.330
<b>那一刻 我们就像造物主</b><b>
We were the lords of all creation.</b>

38:08.900 --> 38:10.240
<b>至于安迪</b><b>
As for Andy...</b>

38:10.740 --> 38:13.070
<b>他蜷坐在阴凉里 打发他的时光</b><b>
he spent that break hunkered in the shade...</b>

38:13.570 --> 38:15.810
<b>脸上带着奇异的微笑</b><b>
a strange little smile on his face...</b>

38:16.310 --> 38:18.500
<b>看我们喝他的啤酒</b><b>
watching us drink his beer.</b>

38:26.620 --> 38:27.980
<b>来一瓶吧?</b><b>
Want a cold one?</b>

38:28.650 --> 38:31.590
<b>不 谢谢 我戒酒了</b><b>
No, thanks. I gave up drinking.</b>

38:35.560 --> 38:38.620
<b>你可以说他是想讨好守卫</b><b>
You could argue he done it to curry favor with the guards.</b>

38:39.330 --> 38:43.130
<b>或者是想和我们拉关系</b><b>
Or maybe make a few friends among us cons.</b>

38:43.870 --> 38:44.640
<b>依我看</b><b>
Me?</b>

38:45.140 --> 38:47.870
<b>他这样做只是为了重温一下自由的时光</b><b>
I think he did it just to feel normal again...</b>

38:48.370 --> 38:50.600
<b>哪怕就那么一小会儿</b><b>
if only for a short while.</b>

38:53.240 --> 38:54.340
<b>我成王了</b><b>
IKing me.</b>

38:56.210 --> 38:58.550
<b>象棋 才是王者的游戏</b><b>
- Chess. Now there's a game of kings. - What?</b>

38:59.050 --> 39:00.780
<b>文明 战略 什么?</b><b>
Civilized. Strategic.</b>

39:01.450 --> 39:04.220
<b>还有一大套见鬼的规则 我讨厌规则</b><b>
And a total fucking mystery. I hate it.</b>

39:04.720 --> 39:06.490
<b>改天我教教你吧</b><b>
Let me teach you someday.</b>

39:08.060 --> 39:08.990
<b>好的</b><b>
Sure.</b>

39:09.490 --> 39:10.960
<b>我们可以一起弄个棋盘</b><b>
We could get a board together.</b>

39:11.460 --> 39:14.230
<b>你找对人了 我什么都能弄来 你知道噻?</b><b>
You're talking to the right man. I can get things, right?</b>

39:14.730 --> 39:18.440
<b>棋盘我们可以花钱买 棋子我想自己刻</b><b>
We might do business on a board, and I'll carve the pieces myself.</b>

39:18.940 --> 39:22.240
<b>白棋用雪花石膏 黑棋用皂石 你看怎么样?</b><b>
One side in alabaster, one in soapstone. What do you think?</b>

39:22.840 --> 39:23.940
<b>我看那得花好几年</b><b>
I think it'll take years.</b>

39:24.440 --> 39:26.680
<b>时间不是问题 问题是没有石头</b><b>
Years I got. What I don't have are the rocks.</b>

39:27.180 --> 39:28.850
<b>这院子里能捡到的都太小了</b><b>
Pickings are pretty slim in the yard.</b>

39:29.350 --> 39:31.180
<b>而且大多是鹅卵石</b><b>
Pebbles, mostly.</b>

39:35.520 --> 39:38.320
<b>安迪 我们得算是朋友了吧?</b><b>
We're getting to be kind of friends, aren't we?</b>

39:39.190 --> 39:40.750
<b>我想是的</b><b>
Yeah, I guess.</b>

39:41.390 --> 39:42.920
<b>我能问你个问题吗?</b><b>
Can I ask you something?</b>

39:44.400 --> 39:45.830
<b>你为什么做出那种事?</b><b>
Why'd you do it?</b>

39:47.070 --> 39:48.330
<b>我是被冤枉的 瑞德</b><b>
I'm innocent, Red.</b>

39:48.830 --> 39:50.860
<b>跟这儿其他人一样</b><b>
Just like everybody else here.</b>

39:55.210 --> 39:56.760
<b>你是怎么进来的?</b><b>
What are you in for?</b>

39:59.480 --> 40:01.350
<b>和你一样 谋杀</b><b>
Murder. Same as you.</b>

40:01.850 --> 40:03.010
<b>被冤枉的?</b><b>
Innocent?</b>

40:05.720 --> 40:08.120
<b>肖申克唯一有罪的人</b><b>
Only guilty man in Shawshank.</b>

41:07.450 --> 41:08.650
<b>她在哪儿唱歌呢?</b><b>
Where's the canary?</b>

41:09.150 --> 41:10.150
<b>你怎么知道的?</b><b>
How did you know?</b>

41:10.650 --> 41:11.630
<b>我知道什么了?</b><b>
- How did I know what? - So you don't know.</b>

41:12.130 --> 41:14.310
<b>这么说你不知道? 跟我来!</b><b>
Come.</b>

41:16.820 --> 41:18.910
<b>她就在里面</b><b>
This is where the canary is.</b>

41:21.590 --> 41:24.930
<b>听到我家里有女人唱歌很惊讶是吗?</b><b>
Quite a surprise to hear a woman singing in my house, eh?</b>

41:28.430 --> 41:29.830
<b>的确非常令我...</b><b>
That's quite a...</b>

41:30.770 --> 41:32.430
<b>惊讶</b><b>
surprise.</b>

41:34.930 --> 41:36.740
<b>瑞德</b><b>
Red.</b>

41:36.740 --> 41:38.140
<b>等一下 先别说话</b><b>
Wait, wait.</b>

41:38.680 --> 41:39.950
<b>她出场了</b><b>
Here she comes.</b>

41:40.450 --> 41:43.010
<b>我太喜欢看她摆弄头发那副骚样儿了</b><b>
I like this part when she does that shit with her hair.</b>

41:43.510 --> 41:45.950
<b>我知道 这个月已经看了三遍了</b><b>
I know. I've seen it three times this month.</b>

41:46.450 --> 41:48.350
<b>吉尔达 你打扮好了吗?</b><b>
Gilda, are you decent?</b>

41:49.350 --> 41:50.480
<b>我?</b><b>
Me?</b>

41:53.190 --> 41:54.950
<b>天呐 爱死啦</b><b>
God, I love it.</b>

42:00.130 --> 42:03.120
<b>我知道你有办法弄东西进来</b><b>
I understand you're a man that knows how to get things.</b>

42:04.140 --> 42:07.570
<b>这事儿大家一向都知道 你想要什么?</b><b>
I'm known to locate certain things from time to time. What do you want?</b>

42:08.070 --> 42:10.200
<b>- 丽塔·海华斯 - 什么?</b><b>
- Rita Hayworth. - What?</b>

42:10.780 --> 42:12.140
<b>你能搞到她吗?</b><b>
Can you get her?</b>

42:13.540 --> 42:16.910
<b>这么说你就是强尼了 久闻大名</b><b>
So this is Johnny Farrel. I've heard a lot about you.</b>

42:18.150 --> 42:20.150
<b>- 你得等几个星期 - 那么久?</b><b>
- Take a few weeks. - Weeks?</b>

42:20.650 --> 42:25.050
<b>我这分钟又没把她藏在裤裆里 抱歉我这么粗鲁</b><b>
I don't have her stuffed down the front of my pants right now, sorry to say.</b>

42:25.620 --> 42:26.660
<b>但我能拿到</b><b>
But I'll get her.</b>

42:27.160 --> 42:28.490
<b>放心好了!</b><b>
Relax.</b>

42:30.360 --> 42:31.660
<b>谢谢!</b><b>
Thanks.</b>

42:52.250 --> 42:53.750
<b>- 出去遛遛腿! - 可是我得换带子!</b><b>
- Get out! - I got to change reels!</b>

42:54.250 --> 42:56.240
<b>我叫你他妈的滚出去!</b><b>
I said fuck off!</b>

43:02.390 --> 43:03.760
<b>你不打算尖叫吗?</b><b>
Ain't you going to scream?</b>

43:05.100 --> 43:06.960
<b>我们做个了断吧!</b><b>
Let's get this over with.</b>

43:12.070 --> 43:14.060
<b>操 我鼻梁断了!</b><b>
He broke my fucking nose!</b>

43:23.380 --> 43:24.580
<b>现在</b><b>
Now...</b>

43:25.080 --> 43:27.020
<b>我要拉开拉链</b><b>
I'm going to open my fly...</b>

43:27.520 --> 43:30.280
<b>我给你吞什么你就吞什么</b><b>
and you'll swallow what I give you to swallow.</b>

43:31.420 --> 43:33.730
<b>然后是罗斯 你把他鼻子打坏了</b><b>
Then you'll swallow Rooster's. You broke his nose.</b>

43:34.230 --> 43:36.060
<b>他得找点补偿回来</b><b>
He ought to have something to show for it.</b>

43:36.560 --> 43:38.130
<b>你的命根子到我嘴里就会跟你分家</b><b>
You put it in my mouth, you lose it.</b>

43:38.630 --> 43:41.070
<b>不 你还没明白</b><b>
No, you don't understand.</b>

43:41.570 --> 43:44.300
<b>你敢那样 我就把这八英寸全部插到你耳朵里</b><b>
Do that and I'll put all eight inches of this in your ear.</b>

43:44.800 --> 43:47.970
<b>行啊 但你得知道大脑受到重创时</b><b>
All right, but you should know that sudden, serious brain injury...</b>

43:48.470 --> 43:50.110
<b>会让受害人拼命咬牙</b><b>
causes the victim to bite down hard.</b>

43:50.610 --> 43:54.100
<b>实话告诉你 这种咬劲儿之大</b><b>
In fact, I hear the bite reflex is so strong...</b>

43:54.910 --> 43:58.950
<b>得用铁棍才能把他的嘴巴撬开</b><b>
they have to pry the victim's jaws open...with a crowbar.</b>

44:01.920 --> 44:03.150
<b>你他妈从哪儿知道的?</b><b>
Where do you get this shit?</b>

44:03.650 --> 44:05.050
<b>看书看的</b><b>
I read it.</b>

44:06.640 --> 44:08.840
<b>不识字? 你这无知的杂种!</b><b>
illiterate? You ignorant fuck!</b>

44:10.800 --> 44:11.890
<b>哦宝贝儿</b><b>
Honey!</b>

44:13.830 --> 44:15.560
<b>你错了</b><b>
You shouldn't!</b>

44:18.240 --> 44:20.910
<b>伯格斯没把任何东西放进安迪的嘴里</b><b>
Bogs didn't put anything in Andy's mouth.</b>

44:21.410 --> 44:23.410
<b>他的同伙也没有</b><b>
And neither did his friends.</b>

44:23.910 --> 44:27.740
<b>他们只是把他打了个半死</b><b>
What they did do is beat him within an inch of his life.</b>

44:28.410 --> 44:30.900
<b>安迪在医务所躺了一个月</b><b>
Andy spent a month in the infirmary.</b>

44:31.720 --> 44:34.240
<b>伯格斯则被关了一周的小黑屋</b><b>
Bogs spent a week in the hole.</b>

44:38.320 --> 44:39.850
<b>伯格斯 时间到了</b><b>
Time's up, Bogs.</b>

44:43.660 --> 44:45.320
<b>遵命 头儿</b><b>
It's your world, boss.</b>

44:48.600 --> 44:51.100
<b>马上返回本人牢房 准备点名</b><b>
Return to your cellblocks for evening count.</b>

44:51.600 --> 44:54.260
<b>所有人犯返回牢房点名</b><b>
All prisoners report for lock down.</b>

45:09.190 --> 45:10.210
<b>干嘛?</b><b>
What?</b>

45:22.870 --> 45:25.390
<b>- 他要往哪儿跑? - 拽着脚脖子!</b><b>
- Where's he going? - Grab his ankles.</b>

45:27.450 --> 45:32.470
<b>不要! 不要!... 救命!</b><b>
No! No!... Help!</b>

45:36.150 --> 45:38.520
<b>从那以后 有两件事再也没发生过了</b><b>
Two things never happened again after that.</b>

45:39.020 --> 45:42.140
<b>姐妹们再也没碰过安迪一下</b><b>
The Sisters never laid a finger on Andy again.</b>

45:42.990 --> 45:45.480
<b>伯格斯再也没有站起来</b><b>
And Bogs would never walk again.</b>

45:46.660 --> 45:49.860
<b>他被送到北部一所低监护医院</b><b>
They transferred him to a minimum-security hospital upstate.</b>

45:50.360 --> 45:52.830
<b>据我所知 他的下半辈子</b><b>
To my knowledge, he lived out the rest of his days...</b>

45:53.330 --> 45:55.160
<b>都只能靠一根吃流食的吸管来维持了</b><b>
drinking his food through a straw.</b>

45:56.170 --> 46:00.260
<b>安迪从医务所出来时应该送他个见面礼</b><b>
Andy could use a nice welcome back when he gets out of the infirmary.</b>

46:02.010 --> 46:03.340
<b>好主意</b><b>
Sounds good to us.</b>

46:03.840 --> 46:06.330
<b>我们还欠着他的啤酒呢</b><b>
I figure we owe him that much for the beer.</b>

46:07.080 --> 46:09.340
<b>这小子喜欢下象棋</b><b>
The man likes to play chess.</b>

46:09.850 --> 46:11.750
<b>咱们给他找些石头吧</b><b>
Let's get him some rocks.</b>

46:44.380 --> 46:45.610
<b>伙计们</b><b>
Guys!</b>

46:46.380 --> 46:47.150
<b>我找到一块</b><b>
I got one.</b>

46:47.650 --> 46:49.140
<b>我找到一块 你们看</b><b>
I got one. Look!</b>

46:51.060 --> 46:54.830
<b>海伍德 那不是肥皂石 也不是雪花石膏</b><b>
Heywood, that isn't soapstone! And it ain't alabaster either.</b>

46:55.330 --> 46:56.930
<b>你当你是他妈的搞地质的吗?</b><b>
What are you, a fucking geologist?</b>

46:57.430 --> 46:58.860
<b>他说的没错 那真不是</b><b>
He's right. It ain't.</b>

46:59.360 --> 47:02.260
<b>- 那他妈这是什么玩意儿? - 那是马儿的苹果</b><b>
- What the hell is it then? - It's a horse apple.</b>

47:03.230 --> 47:07.300
<b>Bullshit：字面意思为"牛粪"</b>

47:03.230 --> 47:07.300
<b>- 胡扯! - 不是牛粪 是风干的马粪</b><b>
- Bullshit! - No, horseshit. Petrified.</b>

47:16.310 --> 47:17.320
<b>妈的</b><b>
Damn!</b>

47:17.820 --> 47:21.750
<b>尽管开始不是太顺 但很快大伙便就轻架熟了</b><b>
Despite a few hitches, the boys came through in fine style.</b>

47:22.250 --> 47:23.960
<b>到安迪要回来的那个星期</b><b>
And by the week Andy was due back...</b>

47:24.460 --> 47:28.150
<b>我们找到的石头已经多得够他忙活一辈子了</b><b>
we had enough rocks saved up to keep him busy till rapture.</b>

47:28.990 --> 47:31.260
<b>同时 那个星期到了一大批货</b><b>
Also got a big shipment in that week.</b>

47:31.760 --> 47:32.600
<b>香烟</b><b>
Cigarettes...</b>

47:33.100 --> 47:33.830
<b>口香糖</b><b>
chewing gum...</b>

47:34.330 --> 47:35.500
<b>威士忌</b><b>
sipping whisky...</b>

47:36.000 --> 47:39.100
<b>印有裸体女人的扑克牌 随便你叫它什么吧</b><b>
playing cards with naked ladies on them. You name it.</b>

47:39.600 --> 47:42.330
<b>当然 最重要的东西</b><b>
And of course, the most important item:</b>

47:44.210 --> 47:46.270
<b>丽塔·海华斯她本人</b><b>
Rita Hayworth herself.</b>

48:09.380 --> 48:11.710
<b>欢迎归来 免费享用</b>

48:23.380 --> 48:25.350
<b>注意 要查房了</b><b>
Heads up. They're tossing cells.</b>

48:25.850 --> 48:28.550
<b>注意 要查房了</b><b>
Heads up. They're tossing cells!</b>

48:29.200 --> 48:31.640
<b>119号</b><b>
119.</b>

48:33.490 --> 48:35.150
<b>123号</b><b>
123.</b>

48:37.060 --> 48:39.190
<b>《圣经》</b>

48:45.600 --> 48:46.430
<b>站好</b><b>
On your feet.</b>

48:49.070 --> 48:50.560
<b>面朝墙壁</b><b>
Face the wall.</b>

49:24.710 --> 49:26.610
<b>向后转 面朝典狱长</b><b>
Turn around and face the warden.</b>

49:33.220 --> 49:35.280
<b>看见你在念经 我很欣慰</b><b>
Pleased to see you reading this.</b>

49:36.620 --> 49:38.550
<b>喜欢哪一段?</b><b>
Any favorite passages?</b>

49:39.420 --> 49:44.220
<b>"所以汝当警醒 因汝不知屋主何时到来!"</b><b>
"Watch ye, therefore, for ye know not...when the master of the house cometh."</b>

49:45.360 --> 49:47.520
<b>马可福音十三章三十五节</b><b>
Mark 13:35.</b>

49:48.270 --> 49:50.130
<b>我一直很喜欢这一段</b><b>
I've always liked that one.</b>

49:51.070 --> 49:52.700
<b>但我更喜欢...</b><b>
But I prefer...</b>

49:53.200 --> 49:58.540
<b>"我是世界之光 跟随我的人不会行于黑暗 还会拥有生命之光!"</b><b>
" I am the light of the world. Ye that followeth me shall have the light of life."</b>

49:59.040 --> 50:01.450
<b>约翰福音八章十二节</b><b>
John, chapter 8, verse 12.</b>

50:01.950 --> 50:03.680
<b>我听说你精通数字</b><b>
I hear you're good with numbers.</b>

50:04.180 --> 50:05.170
<b>非常好</b><b>
How nice.</b>

50:06.420 --> 50:08.350
<b>人应该有一技之长</b><b>
Man should have a skill.</b>

50:10.890 --> 50:11.910
<b>这是拿来干嘛的?</b><b>
Explain this.</b>

50:13.090 --> 50:17.100
<b>这是石垫 打磨石头用的</b><b>
It's called a rock blanket. It's for shaping and polishing rocks.</b>

50:17.600 --> 50:19.500
<b>我的一点小嗜好</b><b>
A little hobby of mine.</b>

50:30.370 --> 50:31.580
<b>相当干净</b><b>
It's pretty clean.</b>

50:32.080 --> 50:35.170
<b>有点违禁品 但不会导致严重后果</b><b>
Some contraband here, but nothing to get in a twist over.</b>

50:39.520 --> 50:41.510
<b>这我可不会同意</b><b>
I can't say I approve of this.</b>

50:43.150 --> 50:44.620
<b>但我想</b><b>
But I suppose...</b>

50:46.690 --> 50:48.680
<b>凡事总有例外</b><b>
exceptions can be made.</b>

50:59.070 --> 51:00.400
<b>锁门!</b><b>
Lock them up!</b>

51:03.310 --> 51:04.810
<b>差点忘了</b><b>
I almost forgot.</b>

51:05.310 --> 51:07.470
<b>我不能从你这儿带走这个</b><b>
I'd hate to deprive you of this.</b>

51:08.210 --> 51:09.850
<b>得救之道就在其中</b><b>
Salvation lies within.</b>

51:10.350 --> 51:11.410
<b>是的 先生</b><b>
Yes, sir.</b>

51:19.960 --> 51:22.490
<b>查房其实只是个借口</b><b>
Tossing cells was just an excuse.</b>

51:22.990 --> 51:26.900
<b>事实上 诺顿是想称称安迪的斤两</b><b>
Truth is...Norton wanted to size Andy up.</b>

51:34.010 --> 51:36.480
<b>主的审判将会迅速降临</b>

51:40.580 --> 51:42.910
<b>我太太在教会做的</b><b>
My wife made that in church group.</b>

51:45.580 --> 51:46.880
<b>很漂亮 先生</b><b>
Very nice, sir.</b>

51:48.450 --> 51:49.920
<b>喜欢洗衣房的工作吗?</b><b>
You enjoy working the laundry?</b>

51:51.590 --> 51:53.120
<b>不 先生 不怎么喜欢</b><b>
No, sir. Not especially.</b>

51:53.620 --> 51:58.760
<b>或许我们可以找点别的更适合发挥你的学识的工作</b><b>
Perhaps we can find something more...befitting a man of your education.</b>

52:06.840 --> 52:08.330
<b>杰克 布鲁克斯呢?</b><b>
Hey, Jake. Where's Brooks?</b>

52:09.100 --> 52:09.470
<b>安迪</b><b>
</b>

52:10.170 --> 52:12.940
<b>我就知道是你来了</b><b>
I thought I heard you out here.</b>

52:13.610 --> 52:14.950
<b>我被派到你这儿来了</b><b>
I've been reassigned to you.</b>

52:15.450 --> 52:17.780
<b>我知道 他们告诉我了</b><b>
I know, they told me.</b>

52:18.620 --> 52:20.380
<b>不会也是被踢过来的吧?</b><b>
Ain't that a kick in the head?</b>

52:20.880 --> 52:22.890
<b>好吧 我带你随便看看</b><b>
Well, I'll give you the dime tour.</b>

52:23.390 --> 52:24.550
<b>来吧</b><b>
Come on.</b>

52:25.960 --> 52:27.390
<b>就是这儿了</b><b>
Well, here she is.</b>

52:27.890 --> 52:29.880
<b>肖申克监狱图书馆</b><b>
The Shawshank Prison Library.</b>

52:30.560 --> 52:32.550
<b>《国家地理》</b><b>
National Geographics...</b>

52:33.460 --> 52:35.970
<b>《读者文摘》精华本</b><b>
Reader's Digest condensed books...</b>

52:36.470 --> 52:38.060
<b>美国著名小说家 作品逾百部 销量超过2亿册</b>

52:36.470 --> 52:38.060
<b>路易斯·L·阿莫尔</b><b>
and Louis L'Amour.</b>

52:38.640 --> 52:40.300
<b>《展望》杂志</b><b>
Look magazine.</b>

52:40.800 --> 52:42.910
<b>美国著名侦探小说作家</b>

52:40.800 --> 52:42.910
<b>厄尔·斯坦利·加德纳</b><b>
Erle Stanley Gardners.</b>

52:43.410 --> 52:46.580
<b>每天晚上我把车子装满 推出去遛一圈</b><b>
Every evening I load up the cart and make my rounds.</b>

52:47.080 --> 52:49.740
<b>在这块板子上记几个名字</b><b>
I enter the names on this clipboard here.</b>

52:50.250 --> 52:52.310
<b>司马光砸缸 小事一桩!</b><b>
Easy, peasy, Japanese-y.</b>

52:52.810 --> 52:56.620
<b>- 有问题吗? - 你作图书管理员有多久了?</b><b>
 - Any questions? - How long have you been librarian?</b>

52:57.820 --> 53:01.850
<b>我1905年入狱 1912年他们安排我作图书管理员</b><b>
I come here in '05, and they made me librarian in 1912.</b>

53:03.160 --> 53:05.100
<b>你以前有助手吗?</b><b>
And have you ever had an assistant?</b>

53:05.600 --> 53:08.000
<b>没有 没什么要帮忙的 真的</b><b>
No. Not much to it, really.</b>

53:08.770 --> 53:09.930
<b>为什么现在? 为什么是我?</b><b>
Why me? Why now?</b>

53:10.430 --> 53:11.440
<b>这我可不知道</b><b>
I don't know.</b>

53:11.940 --> 53:15.710
<b>但有人来这儿和我作个伴我倒非常欢迎 杜弗瑞恩!</b><b>
But it'd be nice to have some company down here.</b>

53:26.220 --> 53:28.510
<b>就是他 你要找的人</b><b>
That's him. That's the one.</b>

53:36.160 --> 53:37.230
<b>我叫迪金斯</b><b>
I'm Dekins.</b>

53:37.730 --> 53:39.360
<b>我一直想...</b><b>
I was thinking...</b>

53:40.030 --> 53:43.900
<b>替我孩子的学业办一份信托基金</b><b>
about setting up some kind of trust fund for my kids' educations.</b>

53:47.810 --> 53:49.270
<b>我明白了</b><b>
I see.</b>

53:51.710 --> 53:52.210
<b>好吧...</b><b>
Well...</b>

53:54.380 --> 53:57.350
<b>让我们坐下来慢慢谈好吗?</b><b>
Why don't we have a seat and talk it over.</b>

53:59.220 --> 54:03.520
<b>布鲁克斯 你能找张纸还有铅笔吗?</b><b>
Do you have a piece of paper and a pencil?</b>

54:14.870 --> 54:16.160
<b>谢谢</b><b>
Thanks.</b>

54:16.830 --> 54:17.890
<b>那么...</b><b>
So...</b>

54:19.670 --> 54:21.400
<b>迪金斯先生</b><b>
Mister Dekins...</b>

54:22.240 --> 54:24.040
<b>接着安迪说 "迪金斯先生...</b><b>
And then Andy says, "Mr. Dekins...</b>

54:24.540 --> 54:27.240
<b>你想让你的儿子去哈佛还是耶鲁?"</b><b>
do you want your sons to go to Harvard or Yale?"</b>

54:27.740 --> 54:28.650
<b>他不可能那么说!</b><b>
He didn't say that!</b>

54:29.150 --> 54:31.420
<b>上帝可以作证</b><b>
As God as my witness!</b>

54:31.920 --> 54:33.350
<b>迪金斯愣了一下</b><b>
Dekins blinked for a second...</b>

54:33.850 --> 54:36.920
<b>然后傻笑起来 他甚至还握了安迪的手</b><b>
then he laughed and actually shook Andy's hand.</b>

54:37.420 --> 54:38.320
<b>扯淡吧!</b><b>
My ass!</b>

54:38.820 --> 54:42.530
<b>握他的手啊! 我跟你们讲 我高兴得差点尿裤子</b><b>
Shook his hand, I tell you, I near soiled myself!</b>

54:43.030 --> 54:47.000
<b>只要穿上西服打起领带 桌子上再来个扭着草裙舞的姑娘</b><b>
All he needed was a suit and tie and a jiggly hula gal on his desk...</b>

54:47.500 --> 54:49.800
<b>安迪就是"杜弗瑞恩先生"了 各位!</b><b>
he'd have been "Mr. Dufresne " if you please.</b>

54:50.300 --> 54:51.930
<b>安迪 交上新朋友了?</b><b>
Making a few friends?</b>

54:53.620 --> 54:58.640
<b>我只是一个可以提供可靠理财计划的犯人</b><b>
I'm a convicted murderer who provides sound financial planning.</b>

54:59.140 --> 55:01.180
<b>也就是个不错的宠物罢了</b><b>
It's a wonderful pet to have.</b>

55:01.680 --> 55:03.480
<b>至少你不用在洗衣房熬着了 对吧?</b><b>
Got you out of the laundry, though.</b>

55:04.010 --> 55:05.650
<b>也许还能多做点事情</b><b>
It might do more than that.</b>

55:06.150 --> 55:08.550
<b>扩大图书馆怎么样 弄些新书进来</b><b>
How about expanding the library. Get some new books.</b>

55:09.050 --> 55:11.650
<b>你有那能耐倒不如弄张台球桌进来</b><b>
If you ask for something, ask for a pool table.</b>

55:13.360 --> 55:16.060
<b>你打算怎么办? 我是说...</b><b>
How do you expect to do that? I mean...</b>

55:16.560 --> 55:19.500
<b>怎么弄来新书 "杜弗瑞恩先生" 不介意的话</b><b>
get new books in here, "Mr. Dufresne, if you please."</b>

55:20.000 --> 55:22.060
<b>我找典狱长要经费</b><b>
I'll ask the warden for funds.</b>

55:22.930 --> 55:26.940
<b>噢 孩子 孩子 我在这儿经历了六个典狱长</b><b>
Six wardens have been through here in my tenure, and I've learned...</b>

55:27.440 --> 55:29.470
<b>我学到一条亘古不变的普世真理</b><b>
one immutable, universal truth:</b>

55:29.970 --> 55:31.080
<b>当你要钱的时候 没有一个典狱长</b><b>
Not one born whose asshole...</b>

55:31.580 --> 55:36.510
<b>不把他们的屁眼绷的跟小军鼓一样紧的</b><b>
wouldn't pucker up tighter than a snare drum when you ask for funds.</b>

55:37.380 --> 55:39.980
<b>- 预算不够用 - 这我了解</b><b>
- The budget's stretched thin as it is. - I see.</b>

55:40.480 --> 55:43.620
<b>或许我可以写信向州参议员申请经费</b><b>
Maybe I could write the state senate and request funds from them.</b>

55:44.120 --> 55:47.930
<b>他们只会花纳税人的钱为监狱做三件事</b><b>
They have only three ways to spend the taxpayers' money for prisons:</b>

55:48.430 --> 55:50.560
<b>加高围墙 修建牢房 增派守卫!</b><b>
More walls, more bars, more guards.</b>

55:51.060 --> 55:53.430
<b>如果您准许 我想试试看 每周写一封信</b><b>
I'd like to try, with permission. A letter a week.</b>

55:53.930 --> 55:56.430
<b>- 他们不能永远不当回事儿 - 他们当然能!</b><b>
- They can't ignore me forever. - Sure can.</b>

55:56.930 --> 55:59.400
<b>但你要是写着高兴那就写吧</b><b>
But you write your letters if it makes you happy.</b>

55:59.900 --> 56:02.500
<b>我替你寄出去 怎么样?</b><b>
I'll even mail them for you. How's that?</b>

56:04.170 --> 56:06.680
<b>于是 安迪开始每周写一封信</b><b>
So Andy started writing a letter a week...</b>

56:07.180 --> 56:08.770
<b>就像他说的那样</b><b>
just like he said.</b>

56:12.950 --> 56:15.290
<b>诺顿说的也没错</b><b>
And like Norton said...</b>

56:15.790 --> 56:17.250
<b>安迪没得到过任何答复</b><b>
Andy got no answers.</b>

56:25.460 --> 56:30.370
<b>到次年四月时 安迪已经在帮肖申克的一半狱警报税了</b><b>
The following April, he did tax returns for half the guards at Shawshank.</b>

56:31.700 --> 56:33.700
<b>又过了一年 所有狱警都来找他帮忙</b><b>
Year after that, he did them all...</b>

56:34.200 --> 56:36.140
<b>包括典狱长的都由他处理了</b><b>
including the warden's.</b>

56:37.870 --> 56:43.980
<b>再过一年 他们甚至把狱警联赛的赛程安排在当年的报税期</b><b>
Year after that, they rescheduled the intramural season...to coincide with tax season.</b>

56:45.550 --> 56:49.720
<b>其它监狱球队的狱警们都带着报税单来打比赛</b><b>
The guards on the opposing teams all remembered to bring their W-2s.</b>

56:50.220 --> 56:51.260
<b>就是说莫尔斯比监狱...</b><b>
So Moresby Prison...</b>

56:51.760 --> 56:53.760
<b>配给你一支枪 但要你自己付钱</b><b>
issued you a gun, but you paid for it.</b>

56:54.260 --> 56:55.660
<b>对 手枪皮套也是</b><b>
Right. The holster too.</b>

56:56.160 --> 56:58.330
<b>那是免税的 你可以把这一项划掉</b><b>
That's tax-deductible. You can write that off.</b>

56:58.830 --> 57:01.860
<b>没错! 安迪完全像一个正规的会计师</b><b>
Yes, sir! Andy was a regular cottage industry.</b>

57:02.570 --> 57:06.840
<b>由于安迪一个人在报税期忙不过来 有必要配个帮手</b><b>
In fact, it got so busy at tax time, he was allowed a staff.</b>

57:07.340 --> 57:09.510
<b>瑞德 你可以拿一叠1040号表格给我吗?</b><b>
Could you hand me a stack of 1040s?</b>

57:10.010 --> 57:14.840
<b>每年能有一个月的时间离开木工车间 对我来说也相当不错</b><b>
Got me out of the wood shop a month out of the year, and that was fine by me.</b>

57:16.080 --> 57:19.240
<b>几年间 寄信那事儿他也从没耽误过</b><b>
And still, he kept sending those letters.</b>

57:23.810 --> 57:27.050
<b>瑞德 安迪 布鲁克斯出事了</b><b>
It's Brooks.</b>

57:28.190 --> 57:29.430
<b>看着门!</b><b>
Watch the door.</b>

57:29.930 --> 57:34.240
<b>- 求你了布鲁克斯 别他妈这么冲动! - 别过来!不要过来!</b><b>
Please, Brooks. - Calm the fuck down. - Stay back! - Stay back, goddamn it! - What's going on?</b>

57:34.740 --> 57:38.870
<b>- 怎么闹成这样? - 才还好好的 不知怎么的就冒把刀出来</b><b>
One second he's fine, then out come the knives.</b>

57:39.370 --> 57:40.940
<b>布鲁克斯 有话好好说 行吗?</b><b>
We can talk about this, right?</b>

57:41.440 --> 57:44.940
<b>没啥好说的 我他妈就是要给他一刀</b><b>
There's nothing to talk about. I'll cut his fucking throat.</b>

57:45.440 --> 57:46.880
<b>先等等 他把你怎么了?</b><b>
What's he done to you?</b>

57:47.380 --> 57:49.040
<b>这是他们逼我的!</b><b>
It's what they done!</b>

57:49.550 --> 57:50.780
<b>我没别的办法</b><b>
I got no choice.</b>

57:51.280 --> 57:53.280
<b>布鲁克斯你不会伤到海伍德的 大家都知道</b><b>
You won't hurt Heywood. We all know that.</b>

57:53.780 --> 57:55.990
<b>- 对吧 海伍德 你知道吧? - 是 没错 我知道</b><b>
- Right, Heywood? - Sure.</b>

57:56.490 --> 57:59.590
<b>你知道他为什么不会伤到你 因为他是你的朋友 布鲁克斯是个讲理的人</b><b>
He's a friend of yours, and Brooks is a reasonable man.</b>

58:00.090 --> 58:01.180
<b>- 对啊, 你说呢? - 是的!</b><b>
Right, guys?</b>

58:02.130 --> 58:03.570
<b>你把刀放下 布鲁克斯</b><b>
So put the knife down. Look at me.</b>

58:04.070 --> 58:07.130
<b>看着我布鲁克斯 把刀放下</b><b>
Put the knife down.</b>

58:08.040 --> 58:11.160
<b>布鲁克斯? 你看看他的脖子 看在上帝份儿上</b><b>
Look at his neck, for God's sake.</b>

58:11.900 --> 58:14.230
<b>布鲁克斯你看他的脖子 他流血了</b><b>
Look at his neck. He's bleeding.</b>

58:15.140 --> 58:16.310
<b>这是唯一可以...</b><b>
It's the only way...</b>

58:16.810 --> 58:18.640
<b>留在这儿的办法</b><b>
they'd let me stay.</b>

58:19.140 --> 58:21.250
<b>你这是糊涂了 你肯定不想这样</b><b>
This is crazy. You don't want to do this.</b>

58:21.750 --> 58:23.800
<b>松手 放下刀</b><b>
Put it, put it down.</b>

58:32.590 --> 58:34.080
<b>别紧张</b><b>
Take it easy.</b>

58:34.760 --> 58:35.790
<b>你不会有事的</b><b>
You'll be all right.</b>

58:36.290 --> 58:38.660
<b>他没事? 那我呢?</b><b>
Him? What about me?</b>

58:39.160 --> 58:41.270
<b>他妈的这个老疯子差点割断我的喉咙</b><b>
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!</b>

58:41.770 --> 58:43.370
<b>你刮胡子弄烂的口子也不止这么大</b><b>
You've had worse from shaving.</b>

58:43.870 --> 58:45.670
<b>你到底怎么把他惹毛的?</b><b>
What did you do to set him off?</b>

58:46.170 --> 58:48.400
<b>没惹啊 我过来和他道个别而已</b><b>
Nothing. I come in here to say farewell.</b>

58:49.010 --> 58:51.670
<b>你不知道啊? 他的假释批下来了</b><b>
Ain't you heard? His parole's come through.</b>

58:54.010 --> 58:56.510
<b>我真搞不懂这是怎么回事</b><b>
I just don't understand what happened in there.</b>

58:57.010 --> 58:59.520
<b>老家伙发疯了 就像一只痰盂里的老鼠</b><b>
Old man's crazy as a rat in a tin shithouse.</b>

59:00.020 --> 59:01.620
<b>海伍德你别没完没了</b><b>
That's enough out of you.</b>

59:02.120 --> 59:04.620
<b>- 我听说把你吓尿裤子了 - 去你的</b><b>
- Heard he had you shitting your pants. - Fuck you.</b>

59:05.120 --> 59:06.320
<b>不说话会死啊!</b><b>
Would you knock it off.</b>

59:07.290 --> 59:08.720
<b>布鲁克斯没发神经</b><b>
Brooks ain't no bug.</b>

59:09.300 --> 59:14.330
<b>他只不过是...他只不过是被体制化了罢了</b><b>
He's just institutionalized.</b>

59:15.700 --> 59:17.330
<b>体制化个鸡毛</b><b>
"Institutionalized " my ass.</b>

59:17.830 --> 59:21.540
<b>老头儿在这儿呆了五十年了 海伍德 五十年!</b><b>
The man's been in here 50 years, Heywood, 50 years!</b>

59:22.040 --> 59:23.470
<b>他就认识这个地方</b><b>
This is all he knows.</b>

59:23.970 --> 59:25.980
<b>在这儿 他是个有地位的人</b><b>
In here, he's an important man...</b>

59:26.480 --> 59:27.570
<b>一个有教养的人</b><b>
an educated man.</b>

59:28.380 --> 59:30.310
<b>到了外面 他什么都不是</b><b>
Outside, he's nothing.</b>

59:31.180 --> 59:34.390
<b>只是个双手患有关节炎的假释犯</b><b>
Just a used-up con with arthritis in both hands.</b>

59:34.890 --> 59:37.660
<b>可能连一张图书馆的借书证都申请不到</b><b>
Probably couldn't get a library card if he tried.</b>

59:38.160 --> 59:39.660
<b>你听懂我说的话没有?</b><b>
You know what I'm trying to say?</b>

59:40.160 --> 59:43.060
<b>瑞德 我听懂了 你说的全是屁话</b><b>
I do believe you're talking out of your ass.</b>

59:44.330 --> 59:46.560
<b>信不信随你大小便</b><b>
You believe whatever you want.</b>

59:47.160 --> 59:49.560
<b>但我得告诉你 这些围墙很吊诡</b><b>
But I tell you these walls are funny.</b>

59:51.170 --> 59:52.830
<b>刚来的时候 你会恨它</b><b>
First you hate them.</b>

59:54.670 --> 59:56.570
<b>慢慢你就会习惯它</b><b>
Then you get used to them.</b>

59:58.510 --> 1:00:00.500
<b>日子久了...</b><b>
Enough time passes...</b>

1:00:01.180 --> 1:00:03.170
<b>你会发现你离不开它</b><b>
you get so you depend on them.</b>

1:00:04.180 --> 1:00:06.080
<b>那就是被体制化了</b><b>
That's "institutionalized."</b>

1:00:06.580 --> 1:00:09.320
<b>操! 我永远不可能爱上这堵破墙</b><b>
Shit. I could never get like that. - Oh, yeah?</b>

1:00:09.820 --> 1:00:13.960
<b>是吗? 这话等你在这儿呆够布鲁克斯那么久再说</b><b>
Wait till you've been here as long as Brooks.</b>

1:00:14.460 --> 1:00:16.020
<b>太他妈对了</b><b>
Goddamn right.</b>

1:00:18.600 --> 1:00:20.530
<b>他们把你送进来渡过余生</b><b>
They send you here for life...</b>

1:00:21.200 --> 1:00:23.530
<b>那也正是他们想要剥夺的</b><b>
that's exactly what they take.</b>

1:00:25.270 --> 1:00:27.260
<b>总之 去日无多</b><b>
Part that counts, anyway.</b>

1:00:34.880 --> 1:00:37.810
<b>我不能再照顾你了 杰克</b><b>
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.</b>

1:00:38.980 --> 1:00:40.640
<b>你现在走吧</b><b>
You go on now.</b>

1:00:41.890 --> 1:00:43.380
<b>你自由了</b><b>
You're free.</b>

1:00:44.650 --> 1:00:46.210
<b>你自由了</b><b>
You're free.</b>

1:01:05.240 --> 1:01:06.900
<b>布鲁克斯 祝你好运</b><b>
Good luck, Brooksie.</b>

1:01:44.880 --> 1:01:46.150
<b>亲爱的伙计们</b><b>
Dear fellas:</b>

1:01:46.650 --> 1:01:50.850
<b>我没法相信外面的东西怎么会跑那么快</b><b>
I can't believe how fast things move on the outside.</b>

1:01:52.160 --> 1:01:54.820
<b>老头 找死啊?</b><b>
Watch it, old-timer! Want to get killed?</b>

1:01:56.060 --> 1:01:59.550
<b>我小时候就见过一次汽车</b><b>
I saw an automobile once when I was a kid...</b>

1:02:00.200 --> 1:02:02.630
<b>但现在这东西无处不在</b><b>
but now they're everywhere.</b>

1:02:06.300 --> 1:02:10.600
<b>全世界都他妈忙得不可开交</b><b>
The world went and got itself in a big damn hurry.</b>

1:02:26.420 --> 1:02:31.860
<b>假释委员会安排我住在一家小旅馆 叫 Brewster</b><b>
The parole board got me into this halfway house...called "The Brewster"...</b>

1:02:32.360 --> 1:02:36.700
<b>还有一份差事 在Food-Way超市替顾客打包</b><b>
and a job...bagging groceries at the Food-Way.</b>

1:02:38.230 --> 1:02:40.370
<b>活儿很忙 我很努力</b><b>
It's hard work and I try to keep up...</b>

1:02:40.870 --> 1:02:43.040
<b>但我这双手总是酸痛不已</b><b>
but my hands hurt most of the time.</b>

1:02:43.540 --> 1:02:45.210
<b>让你的人给我多套一个袋子</b><b>
Make sure your man double-bags.</b>

1:02:45.710 --> 1:02:47.730
<b>上回给我的单层袋子底儿差点烂完了</b><b>
Last time, the bottom near came out.</b>

1:02:48.410 --> 1:02:51.050
<b>按那位女士说的多套一个袋子 懂了吗?</b><b>
Make sure you double-bag like the lady says. Understand?</b>

1:02:51.550 --> 1:02:52.620
<b>是的 先生 我会的</b><b>
Yes, sir. Surely will.</b>

1:02:53.120 --> 1:02:56.640
<b>看得出那经理对我不太感冒</b><b>
I don't think the store manager likes me very much.</b>

1:02:59.660 --> 1:03:03.890
<b>有时下了班以后 我会去公园里喂喂鸽子</b><b>
Sometimes after work, I go to the park and feed the birds.</b>

1:03:04.390 --> 1:03:05.630
<b>我一直在念叨</b><b>
I keep thinking...</b>

1:03:06.130 --> 1:03:09.460
<b>杰克说不定会飞来和我打个招呼</b><b>
Jake might just show up and say hello.</b>

1:03:10.070 --> 1:03:12.060
<b>但它从没来过</b><b>
But he never does.</b>

1:03:13.270 --> 1:03:18.140
<b>我希望 不管在哪 它都能过的好 交到新朋友</b><b>
I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay and making new friends.</b>

1:03:21.750 --> 1:03:24.280
<b>夜里我总是睡不好</b><b>
I have trouble sleeping at night.</b>

1:03:24.780 --> 1:03:27.820
<b>老是做恶梦 身体像一直往下掉</b><b>
I have bad dreams like I'm falling.</b>

1:03:28.320 --> 1:03:30.250
<b>醒来时万分恐惧</b><b>
I wake up scared.</b>

1:03:30.750 --> 1:03:34.990
<b>经常要想一会儿才知道自己在哪儿</b><b>
Sometimes it takes me a while to remember where I am.</b>

1:03:36.490 --> 1:03:41.200
<b>也许我该搞把枪把 Food- Way抢了 好让他们送我回家</b><b>
Maybe I should get a gun and rob the Food-Way so they'd send me home.</b>

1:03:41.700 --> 1:03:46.030
<b>顺便给那个经理来一枪 就当是锦上添花</b><b>
I could shoot the manager while I was at it. Sort of like a bonus.</b>

1:03:47.700 --> 1:03:51.440
<b>可是我已经太老了 再也干不了这种蠢事了</b><b>
I guess I'm too old for that sort of nonsense anymore.</b>

1:03:51.940 --> 1:03:53.380
<b>我不喜欢这地方</b><b>
I don't like it here.</b>

1:03:53.880 --> 1:03:57.870
<b>我觉得很疲惫 不想继续这样成天提心吊胆的 我决定...</b><b>
I'm tired of being afraid all the time. I've decided...</b>

1:03:58.720 --> 1:04:00.380
<b>不这么耗着了</b><b>
not to stay.</b>

1:04:11.290 --> 1:04:13.560
<b>我想他们是不会大惊小怪的</b><b>
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss...</b>

1:04:14.060 --> 1:04:17.560
<b>为我这种老不死的犯不上</b><b>
not for an old crook like me.</b>

1:05:04.500 --> 1:05:08.190
<b>布鲁克斯在这儿住过</b>

1:05:20.030 --> 1:05:24.300
<b>我猜他们是不会大惊小怪的 为我这种老不死的犯不上</b><b>
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss, not for an old crook like me.</b>

1:05:25.340 --> 1:05:28.870
<b>另外 还得向海伍德道个歉 请原谅我上次用刀顶着你脖子</b><b>
P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry I put a knife to his throat.</b>

1:05:29.370 --> 1:05:31.700
<b>这样我也就安心了 布鲁克斯</b><b>
No hard feelings. Brooks."</b>

1:05:42.190 --> 1:05:44.150
<b>他应该死在这儿的</b><b>
He should have died in here.</b>

1:05:49.690 --> 1:05:50.790
<b>你他妈搞什么东东?</b><b>
What the fuck have you done?</b>

1:05:51.290 --> 1:05:53.960
<b>简直他妈乱成一锅粥了</b><b>
It's a goddamn mess, I'll tell you that.</b>

1:05:59.500 --> 1:06:03.230
<b>- 这些都是什么? - 我怎么知道 全他妈是寄给你的</b><b>
- What's all this? - You tell me. They're addressed to you.</b>

1:06:04.510 --> 1:06:05.840
<b>看看吧</b><b>
Take it.</b>

1:06:14.380 --> 1:06:15.870
<b>"亲爱的杜弗瑞恩先生</b><b>
"Dear Mr. Dufresne:</b>

1:06:17.020 --> 1:06:18.690
<b>应阁下来函所请事由 州政府特拨付</b><b>
In response to your inquiries...</b>

1:06:19.190 --> 1:06:23.450
<b>贵图书馆项目经费一笔...</b><b>
the state has allocated the enclosed funds for your library project."</b>

1:06:24.230 --> 1:06:25.760
<b>200美元...</b><b>
This is $ 200.</b>

1:06:26.260 --> 1:06:29.970
<b>此外 州立图书馆亦慷慨捐助</b><b>
"In addition, the library district has generously responded...</b>

1:06:30.470 --> 1:06:32.740
<b>旧书暨杂物一批</b><b>
with a donation of used books and sundries.</b>

1:06:33.240 --> 1:06:37.070
<b>我们相信上述款物足以满足阁下所需 此事就此告一段落</b><b>
We trust this will fill your needs. We now consider the matter closed.</b>

1:06:37.570 --> 1:06:39.110
<b>恳请阁下勿复来函"</b><b>
Please stop sending us letters."</b>

1:06:39.610 --> 1:06:42.010
<b>典狱长回来之前清理干净</b><b>
Clear all this out before the warden gets back.</b>

1:06:42.510 --> 1:06:43.670
<b>知道了</b><b>
Yes, sir.</b>

1:06:47.950 --> 1:06:49.110
<b>干得好安迪!</b><b>
Good for you, Andy.</b>

1:06:52.090 --> 1:06:53.210
<b>哇哦!</b><b>
Wow!</b>

1:06:54.420 --> 1:06:56.360
<b>只用了六年时间</b><b>
It only took six years.</b>

1:06:57.930 --> 1:07:00.360
<b>现在开始 我每星期写两封信</b><b>
From now on, I'll write two letters a week instead of one.</b>

1:07:00.860 --> 1:07:05.000
<b>你可真够倔的 你最好照他说的把这儿收拾干净</b><b>
I believe you're crazy enough. Get this stuff out...like he said.</b>

1:07:05.500 --> 1:07:06.600
<b>我现在去撇大条</b><b>
I've got to pinch a loaf.</b>

1:07:07.100 --> 1:07:08.270
<b>等我出来的时候</b><b>
When I come back...</b>

1:07:08.770 --> 1:07:10.530
<b>不想再见到这些东西 好吗?</b><b>
this is all gone, all right?</b>

1:07:27.380 --> 1:07:28.780
<b>费加罗的婚礼</b>

1:07:59.290 --> 1:08:00.690
<b>安迪 那是什么声音?</b><b>
Do you hear that?</b>

1:09:09.430 --> 1:09:10.590
<b>杜弗瑞恩?</b><b>
Dufresne!</b>

1:09:11.680 --> 1:09:12.220
<b>杜弗瑞恩?</b><b>
</b>

1:09:13.130 --> 1:09:14.650
<b>安迪 让我出去!</b><b>
Andy, let me out!</b>

1:09:17.810 --> 1:09:18.170
<b>安迪?</b><b>
Andy.</b>

1:09:20.670 --> 1:09:21.040
<b>安迪?</b><b>
Andy.</b>

1:09:21.540 --> 1:09:26.280
<b>我至今仍不知晓那两个意大利娘们儿在唱什么</b><b>
I have no idea to this day what those two Italian ladies were singing about.</b>

1:09:26.780 --> 1:09:28.710
<b>话说回来 我也不想知道</b><b>
Truth is, I don't want to know.</b>

1:09:29.210 --> 1:09:31.700
<b>有些东西是无需言传的</b><b>
Some things are best left unsaid.</b>

1:09:35.280 --> 1:09:37.720
<b>我更相信那是因为它的美</b><b>
I like to think it was something so beautiful...</b>

1:09:38.220 --> 1:09:40.060
<b>超出了语言所能形容的范畴</b><b>
it can't be expressed in words...</b>

1:09:40.560 --> 1:09:43.460
<b>它美得让你为之心碎</b><b>
and makes your heart ache because of it.</b>

1:09:45.130 --> 1:09:47.400
<b>我只能告诉你 那声音直入云霄</b><b>
I tell you, those voices soared...</b>

1:09:47.900 --> 1:09:51.900
<b>比这个灰暗角落里任何人所能梦想到的都更高更远</b><b>
higher and farther than anybody in a gray place dares to dream.</b>

1:09:52.400 --> 1:09:55.470
<b>就像一只美丽的小鸟 飞进我们乏味的牢笼</b><b>
It was like a beautiful bird flapped into our drab cage...</b>

1:09:55.970 --> 1:09:58.680
<b>高墙因之消逝于无形之间</b><b>
and made those walls dissolve away.</b>

1:09:59.180 --> 1:10:01.080
<b>就是那一刻</b><b>
And for the briefest of moments...</b>

1:10:01.580 --> 1:10:04.570
<b>每一个关在肖申克的失足者都触摸到了自由</b><b>
every last man at Shawshank felt free.</b>

1:10:07.150 --> 1:10:09.810
<b>但这却惹得典狱长大发雷霆</b><b>
It pissed the warden off something awful.</b>

1:10:11.120 --> 1:10:12.110
<b>把门打开!</b><b>
Open the door.</b>

1:10:15.020 --> 1:10:16.790
<b>开门!</b><b>
Open it up!</b>

1:10:18.090 --> 1:10:20.820
<b>杜弗瑞恩 给我开门!</b><b>
Dufresne, open this door!</b>

1:10:22.170 --> 1:10:23.360
<b>把它关掉!</b><b>
Turn that off!</b>

1:10:30.440 --> 1:10:32.870
<b>我警告你 杜弗瑞恩! 把它关掉!</b><b>
I am warning you. Turn that off!</b>

1:10:46.410 --> 1:10:47.610
<b>小兔乖乖! ; )</b>

1:10:50.630 --> 1:10:52.150
<b>该我收拾你了!</b><b>
You're mine now.</b>

1:10:59.600 --> 1:11:02.540
<b>安迪的惊艳一枪给他带来了两周的禁闭</b><b>
Andy got two weeks in the hole for that little stunt.</b>

1:11:03.040 --> 1:11:04.630
<b>站起来!</b><b>
On your feet.</b>

1:11:05.810 --> 1:11:08.210
<b>- 看看谁来了? - 艺术大师!</b><b>
- Hey, look who's here. - Maestro!</b>

1:11:09.980 --> 1:11:13.480
<b>美国乡村摇滚音乐的标志性人物</b>

1:11:09.980 --> 1:11:13.480
<b>你就不能放点好听的吗 嗯? 比如汉克·威廉姆斯?</b><b>
You couldn't play something good, huh? Like Hank Williams?</b>

1:11:13.980 --> 1:11:16.490
<b>我还没来得及接受点播 他们就冲进来了</b><b>
They broke the door down before I could take requests.</b>

1:11:16.990 --> 1:11:19.820
<b>- 两个星期 犯得上吗? - 我经历过最轻松的一段时光!</b><b>
- Was it worth two weeks? - Easiest time I ever did.</b>

1:11:20.320 --> 1:11:23.480
<b>扯淡 在这破地方就没轻松时光可言 那小黑屋里呆一周就像一年!</b><b>
- Bullshit! No such thing as easy time in the hole. - A week in the hole is like a year.</b>

1:11:23.980 --> 1:11:27.730
<b>是他妈像一年! 我有莫扎特先生陪我!</b><b>
- Damn straight.  - I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.</b>

1:11:28.230 --> 1:11:31.200
<b>他们还能让你背台电唱机进去啊?</b><b>
So they let you tote that record player down there, huh?</b>

1:11:33.640 --> 1:11:35.000
<b>它在我脑子里</b><b>
It was in here.</b>

1:11:35.840 --> 1:11:37.070
<b>在我心里</b><b>
In here.</b>

1:11:38.210 --> 1:11:40.010
<b>这就是音乐的美妙所在 他们...</b><b>
That's the beauty of music. They...</b>

1:11:40.510 --> 1:11:42.840
<b>无法把它从你这儿夺走</b><b>
can't get that from you.</b>

1:11:46.380 --> 1:11:48.750
<b>你们对音乐没有这种感受吗?</b><b>
Haven't you ever felt that way about music?</b>

1:11:50.550 --> 1:11:53.680
<b>我年轻那会儿曾经吹过口琴</b><b>
Well, I played a mean harmonica as a younger man.</b>

1:11:54.720 --> 1:11:55.590
<b>进来以后也就没兴趣了</b><b>
Lost interest in it, though.</b>

1:11:56.090 --> 1:11:58.060
<b>在大牢里没多大意义</b><b>
Didn't make much sense in here.</b>

1:11:58.560 --> 1:11:59.880
<b>这儿才是它最有价值的地方</b><b>
Here's where it makes the most sense.</b>

1:12:00.380 --> 1:12:02.710
<b>有了它你才不会忘记</b><b>
You need it so you don't forget.</b>

1:12:03.210 --> 1:12:04.800
<b>忘记?</b><b>
Forget?</b>

1:12:05.300 --> 1:12:10.040
<b>忘记这世上...有一些地方...不是用石头围起来的</b><b>
Forget that there are...places...</b>

1:12:10.540 --> 1:12:18.380
<b>在你内心深处...有一些东西...</b><b>
in the world that aren't made out of stone. There's something...inside...</b>

1:12:18.880 --> 1:12:24.390
<b>是他们夺不走...摸不到的 只属于你一个人</b><b>
that they can't get to...that they can't touch. That's yours.</b>

1:12:25.920 --> 1:12:27.510
<b>你在说什么?</b><b>
What are you talking about?</b>

1:12:28.560 --> 1:12:29.790
<b>希望</b><b>
Hope.</b>

1:12:30.860 --> 1:12:32.190
<b>希望?</b><b>
Hope.</b>

1:12:34.130 --> 1:12:36.120
<b>我坦白告诉你 我的朋友</b><b>
Let me tell you something, my friend.</b>

1:12:36.930 --> 1:12:39.230
<b>希望是一种危险品</b><b>
Hope is a dangerous thing.</b>

1:12:40.400 --> 1:12:42.740
<b>希望使人疯狂</b><b>
Hope can drive a man insane.</b>

1:12:43.470 --> 1:12:45.310
<b>它在大牢里没有用</b><b>
It's got no use on the inside.</b>

1:12:45.810 --> 1:12:48.000
<b>你得学会接受现实</b><b>
You'd better get used to that idea.</b>

1:12:50.510 --> 1:12:52.000
<b>像布鲁克斯那样?</b><b>
Like Brooks did?</b>

1:13:17.370 --> 1:13:18.360
