<b>州预算委员会投票决定每年拨付款项500元</b><b>
Appropriations Committee voted an annual payment of $500...</b>

1:16:49.280 --> 1:16:50.880
<b>好让他就此闭嘴</b><b>
just to shut him up.</b>

1:16:51.380 --> 1:16:54.090
<b>之后安迪所做的则更让我们瞠目结舌</b><b>
And you'd be amazed how far Andy could stretch it.</b>

1:16:54.590 --> 1:16:57.220
<b>他跟读书会和慈善组织接洽</b><b>
He made deals with book clubs, charity groups.</b>

1:16:57.720 --> 1:17:00.490
<b>论磅买来大量二手书籍</b><b>
He bought remaindered books by the pound...</b>

1:17:00.990 --> 1:17:02.520
<b>《金银岛》</b><b>
Treasure Island.</b>

1:17:03.060 --> 1:17:04.100
<b>罗伯特·路易斯...</b><b>
Robert Louis...</b>

1:17:04.600 --> 1:17:05.330
<b>斯蒂文森</b><b>
Stevenson.</b>

1:17:05.830 --> 1:17:07.200
<b>小说 探险类</b><b>
Fiction, adventure.</b>

1:17:09.770 --> 1:17:10.500
<b>下一本是什么?</b><b>
What's next?</b>

1:17:11.000 --> 1:17:14.060
<b>我这儿是《汽车修理》...</b><b>
I got here Auto Repair...</b>

1:17:14.810 --> 1:17:15.680
<b>和《肥皂雕刻》</b><b>
and Soap Carving.</b>

1:17:16.180 --> 1:17:19.110
<b>职业技术与爱好 属"教育"类 在你后面</b><b>
Trade skills and hobbies. Under "Educational " behind you.</b>

1:17:19.610 --> 1:17:21.450
<b>《基叔山恩仇记》</b><b>
Count of Monte Crisco.</b>

1:17:21.950 --> 1:17:24.250
<b>那是"基督山" 你个笨蛋!</b><b>
That's "Cristo " you dumb shit.</b>

1:17:25.350 --> 1:17:25.680
<b>作者是亚历山大...</b><b>
By Alexandree...</b>

1:17:26.180 --> 1:17:27.920
<b>大种马 (Dum-ass)</b><b>
Dum-ass.</b>

1:17:28.420 --> 1:17:29.450
<b>"大马屁?" (Dumb ass)</b><b>
Dumb ass.</b>

1:17:31.760 --> 1:17:32.820
<b>"大马屁?" </b><b>
Dumb ass?</b>

1:17:35.730 --> 1:17:37.700
<b>大仲马 (Dumas) 知道那是讲什么的吗?</b><b>
Dumas. IKnow what that's about?</b>

1:17:39.970 --> 1:17:41.640
<b>你一定喜欢 它讲的是一次越狱</b><b>
You'd like it. It's about a prison break.</b>

1:17:42.140 --> 1:17:46.040
<b>那我们应该把它归到"教育"类 对吧?</b><b>
We ought to file that under "Educational" too, oughtn't we?</b>

1:17:46.910 --> 1:17:51.000
<b>我们几个则尽我们所能全力帮忙</b><b>
The rest of us did our best to pitch in when and where we could.</b>

1:17:51.580 --> 1:17:53.080
<b>到了肯尼迪遇刺那一年</b><b>
By the year Kennedy was shot...</b>

1:17:53.580 --> 1:17:57.880
<b>安迪已经把一间散发着松节油味道的储藏室</b><b>
Andy had transformed a storage room smelling of turpentine...</b>

1:17:58.380 --> 1:18:01.480
<b>改造成了新英格兰地区最好的的监狱图书馆</b><b>
into the best prison library in New England...</b>

1:18:02.190 --> 1:18:05.120
<b>甚至找得到Hank Williams的精选集唱片</b><b>
complete with a fine selection of Hank Williams.</b>

1:18:12.500 --> 1:18:14.130
<b>那一年也是典狱长诺顿</b><b>
That was also when Warden Norton...</b>

1:18:14.630 --> 1:18:17.540
<b>提出著名的"出监服刑"计划的一年</b><b>
instituted his famous "Inside Out" program.</b>

1:18:18.040 --> 1:18:19.840
<b>也许你看到过这件事的新闻</b><b>
You may remember reading about it.</b>

1:18:20.340 --> 1:18:23.140
<b>当时曾充斥各类报纸 他的照片还上过《展望》杂志</b><b>
It made the papers and got his picture in Look magazine.</b>

1:18:23.640 --> 1:18:24.650
<b>这不是放任自流</b><b>
It's no free ride...</b>

1:18:25.150 --> 1:18:28.080
<b>而是一种真正的 有进步意义的</b><b>
but rather a genuine progressive advance...</b>

1:18:28.580 --> 1:18:30.920
<b>服刑和改造模式</b><b>
in corrections and rehabilitation.</b>

1:18:31.420 --> 1:18:33.650
<b>我们的服刑人员 在适当的监管下</b><b>
Our inmates, properly supervised...</b>

1:18:34.150 --> 1:18:36.490
<b>走出这堵高墙 在外面工作</b><b>
will be put to work outside these walls...</b>

1:18:36.990 --> 1:18:39.790
<b>提供各种形式的公共服务</b><b>
performing all manner of public service.</b>

1:18:40.290 --> 1:18:42.220
<b>他们将懂得诚实劳动的价值</b><b>
These men can learn the value...</b>

1:18:42.720 --> 1:18:46.230
<b>同时他们为社会所提供的服务</b><b>
of an honest day's labor and provide a service to the community...</b>

1:18:46.730 --> 1:18:51.910
<b>对纳税人而言 可将开销降至最低</b><b>
at a bare minimum of expense to Mr. And Mrs. John Q. Taxpayer.</b>

1:18:52.410 --> 1:18:54.440
<b>当然 诺顿不会跟报界说明</b><b>
Of course he didn't tell the press...</b>

1:18:54.940 --> 1:18:58.110
<b>"最低开销"其实是个相当不靠谱的噱头</b><b>
that "bare minimum of expense" is a fairly loose term.</b>

1:18:58.610 --> 1:19:01.350
<b>他有一百种不同的办法暗渡陈仓</b><b>
There are 100 different ways to skim off the top.</b>

1:19:01.850 --> 1:19:04.180
<b>人工 材料 你想怎么算就怎么算</b><b>
Men, materials, you name it.</b>

1:19:04.680 --> 1:19:07.290
<b>哦上帝 金钱就这样滚滚而来!</b><b>
And oh, my Lord, how the money rolled in!</b>

1:19:07.790 --> 1:19:10.020
<b>这样下去 我就没法干了</b><b>
At this rate, you'll put me out of business.</b>

1:19:10.520 --> 1:19:14.960
<b>你守着这些工奴 全城的承包商都没法跟你杀价</b><b>
With this pool of slave labor, you can underbid any contractor in town.</b>

1:19:15.530 --> 1:19:18.200
<b>我们这是在为社会提供有价值的服务</b><b>
We're providing a valuable community service.</b>

1:19:18.700 --> 1:19:22.360
<b>记者当然爱听你这套话 可我还得养家糊口呢</b><b>
That's fine for the papers, but I've got a family to feed.</b>

1:19:23.100 --> 1:19:26.560
<b>山姆...山姆 我们处的时间也不短了</b><b>
We go back a long way.</b>

1:19:27.870 --> 1:19:32.810
<b>我真的需要这份高速公路合同 如果拿不到 说实话我就废了</b><b>
I need this highway contract. I don't get it and I go under. That's a fact.</b>

1:19:33.710 --> 1:19:35.250
<b>你尝尝这些馅饼</b><b>
You have some of this fine pie...</b>

1:19:35.750 --> 1:19:39.080
<b>我老婆特意为你烤的 你就帮帮我吧</b><b>
my missus made for you. You think about that.</b>

1:19:47.360 --> 1:19:49.800
<b>换我是你的话对这个合同不会太担心</b><b>
I wouldn't worry too much about this contract.</b>

1:19:50.300 --> 1:19:53.360
<b>我已经把人手派去干别的了</b><b>
I already got my boys committed elsewhere.</b>

1:19:55.340 --> 1:19:58.400
<b>请一定替我谢谢你太太烤这么好的馅饼</b><b>
You be sure and thank Maisie for this fine pie.</b>

1:19:59.510 --> 1:20:01.510
<b>每一笔暗箱操作</b><b>
And behind every shady deal...</b>

1:20:02.010 --> 1:20:04.410
<b>赚来的每一块钱</b><b>
behind every dollar earned...</b>

1:20:04.910 --> 1:20:07.880
<b>都是由安迪经手做账的</b><b>
there was Andy, keeping the books.</b>

1:20:08.380 --> 1:20:09.380
<b>两笔存款</b><b>
Two deposits.</b>

1:20:09.880 --> 1:20:14.010
<b>缅因州国家银行和新英格兰第一银行 照例办夜间存款</b><b>
Maine National and New England First. Night drops as always, sir.</b>

1:20:44.220 --> 1:20:48.520
<b>把我东西送到洗衣房 两套衣服要干洗 还有古董架上那个包</b><b>
Get my stuff to the laundry. Two suits for dry-clean and a bag of whatnot.</b>

1:20:49.020 --> 1:20:52.260
<b>告诉他们如果再把我的衬衫浆过了头 我就过去教教他们!</b><b>
If they over-starch my shirts again, they'll hear from me.</b>

1:20:52.760 --> 1:20:54.090
<b>- 我看上去怎么样? - 非常好!</b><b>
How do I look?</b>

1:20:55.130 --> 1:20:59.350
<b>波特兰大道有个大型慈善晚会 州长会去!</b><b>
- Very nice. - Big charity to-do up Portland way. Governor will be there.</b>

1:21:00.770 --> 1:21:02.230
<b>剩下这些给你吧?</b><b>
You want the rest of this?</b>

1:21:03.570 --> 1:21:05.500
<b>女人只能烤出恶心的东西</b><b>
Woman can't bake worth shit.</b>

1:21:06.740 --> 1:21:08.070
<b>谢谢你 先生</b><b>
Thank you, sir.</b>

1:21:10.910 --> 1:21:13.850
<b>我听说这样的馅饼他收了不少</b><b>
He's got his fingers in a lot of pies, from what I hear.</b>

1:21:14.350 --> 1:21:18.890
<b>有些手段你做梦都想不到 层层的回扣</b><b>
He's got scams you haven't even dreamed of. IKickbacks on his kickbacks.</b>

1:21:19.390 --> 1:21:21.460
<b>黑钱像河一样流过这里</b><b>
A river of dirty money running through here.</b>

1:21:21.960 --> 1:21:25.490
<b>但他迟早得解释钱是从哪儿来的</b><b>
Sooner or later, he'll have to explain where it came from.</b>

1:21:25.990 --> 1:21:27.760
<b>这就是他用得着我的地方了</b><b>
That's where I come in.</b>

1:21:28.360 --> 1:21:30.360
<b>我让这些钱流通 洗白 汇集</b><b>
I channel it. Filter it. Funnel it.</b>

1:21:30.860 --> 1:21:33.530
<b>股票、证券、国库券...</b><b>
Stocks, securities, tax-free municipals.</b>

1:21:34.030 --> 1:21:37.270
<b>我把钱撒出去 等它们回来的时候...</b><b>
I send it out into the real world, and when it comes back...</b>

1:21:37.770 --> 1:21:40.740
<b>- 干净得就像个处女穴 嗯? - 比那更干净</b><b>
- Clean as a virgin's honeypot, huh? - Cleaner.</b>

1:21:41.340 --> 1:21:44.940
<b>到诺顿退休的时候 我已让他成为百万富翁了</b><b>
By the time Norton retires, I'll have made him a millionaire.</b>

1:21:47.280 --> 1:21:51.380
<b>如果被抓住的话 他岂不是得在这儿给自己编个号儿啊?</b><b>
If they ever catch on, he'll wind up in here wearing a number himself.</b>

1:21:51.880 --> 1:21:54.290
<b>我还以为你很信得过我呢</b><b>
I thought you had more faith in me than that.</b>

1:21:54.790 --> 1:21:57.520
<b>我知道你很能干 但那么多文件总会留下蛛丝马迹</b><b>
I know you're good, but all that paper leaves a trail.</b>

1:21:58.020 --> 1:22:01.130
<b>如果有人想追究 FBI 国税局...</b><b>
Now anybody gets curious, FBI, IRS...</b>

1:22:01.630 --> 1:22:02.560
<b>无论如何</b><b>
whatever.</b>

1:22:03.060 --> 1:22:04.060
<b>总会有人被扯出来</b><b>
It'll lead to somebody.</b>

1:22:04.560 --> 1:22:08.430
<b>那当然 但不会是我 当然也不会是典狱长</b><b>
Sure it is, but not to me, and certainly not to the warden.</b>

1:22:12.810 --> 1:22:13.510
<b>好吧 是谁呢?</b><b>
All right, who?</b>

1:22:14.010 --> 1:22:15.600
<b>兰度·史蒂文!</b><b>
Randall Stevens.</b>

1:22:16.140 --> 1:22:16.780
<b>那是谁?</b><b>
Who?</b>

1:22:17.280 --> 1:22:18.980
<b>沉默寡言的搭档</b><b>
The "silent" silent partner.</b>

1:22:19.480 --> 1:22:22.250
<b>他是那个有罪的人 帐户的所有者</b><b>
He's the guilty one, the man with the bank accounts.</b>

1:22:22.750 --> 1:22:24.620
<b>是洗钱流程的起点</b><b>
It's where the filtering process starts.</b>

1:22:25.120 --> 1:22:27.990
<b>如果有人追查 顶多查到他那儿</b><b>
They trace anything, it'll just lead to him.</b>

1:22:28.590 --> 1:22:29.520
<b>但他是什么人?</b><b>
But who is he?</b>

1:22:30.020 --> 1:22:33.980
<b>他是一个幻影 幽灵 是兔子哈维的二表哥</b><b>
He's a phantom, an apparition. Second cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.</b>

1:22:35.090 --> 1:22:37.830
<b>我凭空...变出来的!</b><b>
I conjured him...out of thin air.</b>

1:22:38.630 --> 1:22:41.360
<b>他只是个活在文件中的人</b><b>
He doesn't exist, except on paper.</b>

1:22:44.440 --> 1:22:46.510
<b>但是你不可能就这么造个人出来</b><b>
You can't just make a person up.</b>

1:22:47.010 --> 1:22:50.100
<b>当然可以 只要你知道制度的运作模式</b><b>
Sure you can, if you know how the system works.</b>

1:22:50.610 --> 1:22:53.280
<b>更令你吃惊的是邮件就能帮你做到</b><b>
It's amazing what you can accomplish by mail.</b>

1:22:53.780 --> 1:22:56.120
<b>史蒂文先生有出生证明书</b><b>
Mr. Stevens has a birth certificate...</b>

1:22:56.620 --> 1:22:58.520
<b>驾驶执照和社保号码</b><b>
driver's license, Social Security.</b>

1:22:59.020 --> 1:22:59.720
<b>你别忽悠我!</b><b>
You're shitting me.</b>

1:23:00.220 --> 1:23:05.230
<b>他们追查帐户 就像是去雕刻一个我想象中的虚幻物</b><b>
If they trace any accounts, they'll wind up chasing...a figment of my imagination.</b>

1:23:05.730 --> 1:23:07.720
<b>靠 果然精英人士!</b><b>
Well, I'll be damned!</b>

1:23:09.060 --> 1:23:10.660
<b>我是不是早就说过你很能干?</b><b>
Did I say you were good?</b>

1:23:11.160 --> 1:23:12.790
<b>荷兰画家 17世纪欧洲最伟大的画家之一</b>

1:23:11.160 --> 1:23:12.790
<b>妈的 你简直是当代伦布兰特</b><b>
Shit, you are Rembrandt.</b>

1:23:13.530 --> 1:23:14.970
<b>讽刺的是</b><b>
The funny thing is...</b>

1:23:15.470 --> 1:23:19.470
<b>在外面 我是个正直的人 宁折不弯</b><b>
on the outside, I was an honest man, straight as an arrow.</b>

1:23:19.970 --> 1:23:22.300
<b>却不得不到监狱里来作一个骗子</b><b>
I had to come to prison to be a crook.</b>

1:23:31.180 --> 1:23:32.480
<b>你苦恼过吗?</b><b>
Ever bother you?</b>

1:23:33.920 --> 1:23:36.760
<b>点子不是我出的 我只是处理收益</b><b>
I don't run the scams. I just process the profits.</b>

1:23:37.260 --> 1:23:39.250
