I don't think so.</b>

1:44:47.590 --> 1:44:51.530
<b>在这儿我当然能替你搞来东西 但是...</b><b>
In here I'm the guy who can get things for you, sure, but...</b>

1:44:52.300 --> 1:44:54.530
<b>在外面你只要有本黄页就成了</b><b>
outside all you need is the Yellow Pages.</b>

1:44:55.030 --> 1:44:57.260
<b>见鬼 我不想知道怎么开始的!</b><b>
Hell, I wouldn't know where to begin.</b>

1:44:59.400 --> 1:45:00.940
<b>太平洋?</b><b>
Pacific Ocean?</b>

1:45:01.440 --> 1:45:02.540
<b>靠!</b><b>
Shit.</b>

1:45:03.040 --> 1:45:04.940
<b>那么大的地方会吓死我的!</b><b>
Scare me to death, something that big.</b>

1:45:05.440 --> 1:45:06.740
<b>我不会!</b><b>
Not me.</b>

1:45:07.950 --> 1:45:10.710
<b>我没杀我妻子 我也没杀她的情人</b><b>
I didn't shoot my wife, and I didn't shoot her lover.</b>

1:45:12.450 --> 1:45:15.680
<b>不论我犯了什么错 我都已补偿过了</b><b>
Whatever mistakes I made, I've paid for them and then some.</b>

1:45:16.720 --> 1:45:18.210
<b>一间酒店 一条船</b><b>
That hotel, that boat...</b>

1:45:19.990 --> 1:45:22.220
<b>我想我要的并不过份!</b><b>
I don't think that's too much to ask.</b>

1:45:27.130 --> 1:45:29.270
<b>我劝你别那么想了</b><b>
You shouldn't be doing this to yourself.</b>

1:45:29.770 --> 1:45:31.740
<b>那只是你的狗屁白日梦!</b><b>
This is just shitty pipe dreams.</b>

1:45:32.240 --> 1:45:34.410
<b>墨西哥远在天边 而你近在眼前!</b><b>
Mexico is way down there and you're in here...</b>

1:45:34.910 --> 1:45:36.310
<b>这是现实!</b><b>
and that's the way it is.</b>

1:45:36.810 --> 1:45:39.640
<b>说的对 这是现实!</b><b>
Yeah, right. That's the way it is.</b>

1:45:41.150 --> 1:45:43.550
<b>它在天边 我在眼前!</b><b>
It's down there and I'm in here.</b>

1:45:46.120 --> 1:45:48.850
<b>该做个简单的选择了!</b><b>
I guess it comes down to a simple choice.</b>

1:45:51.760 --> 1:45:53.250
<b>要么忙着活...</b><b>
Get busy living...</b>

1:45:54.630 --> 1:45:56.650
<b>要么忙着死!</b><b>
or get busy dying.</b>

1:46:00.340 --> 1:46:00.640
<b>安迪!</b><b>
Andy.</b>

1:46:05.180 --> 1:46:05.540
<b>瑞德</b><b>
Red.</b>

1:46:08.770 --> 1:46:11.210
<b>如果你能出去的话 帮我个忙</b><b>
If you ever get out of here, do me a favor.</b>

1:46:11.710 --> 1:46:13.970
<b>没问题 安迪 任何事都行!</b><b>
Sure, Andy. Anything.</b>

1:46:15.850 --> 1:46:19.720
<b>布克斯顿附近有一大片草场 你知道布克斯顿吗?</b><b>
There's a big hayfield up near Buxton. You know where Buxton is?</b>

1:46:21.190 --> 1:46:24.020
<b>那儿有许多草场 有一个很特别...</b><b>
- A lot of hayfields up there. - One in particular.</b>

1:46:24.520 --> 1:46:28.160
<b>它有一段很长的石墙 靠北那头有棵老橡树</b><b>
It's got a long rock wall with a big oak tree at the north end.</b>

1:46:28.660 --> 1:46:31.530
<b>美国著名诗人</b>

1:46:28.660 --> 1:46:31.530
<b>跟罗伯特·弗罗斯特诗里写的差不多</b><b>
It's like something out of a Robert Frost poem.</b>

1:46:32.460 --> 1:46:34.960
<b>那是我向我妻子求婚的地方</b><b>
It's where I asked my wife to marry me.</b>

1:46:36.370 --> 1:46:38.370
<b>我们曾在那儿野餐</b><b>
We went there for a picnic...</b>

1:46:38.870 --> 1:46:40.960
<b>在橡树下亲热</b><b>
and made love under that oak...</b>

1:46:41.640 --> 1:46:43.870
<b>我向她求婚 她答应了</b><b>
and I asked and she said yes.</b>

1:46:47.880 --> 1:46:49.710
<b>答应我 瑞德</b><b>
Promise me, Red.</b>

1:46:50.550 --> 1:46:51.880
<b>如果你能出去</b><b>
If you ever get out...</b>

1:46:52.380 --> 1:46:53.870
<b>找到那地方</b><b>
find that spot.</b>

1:46:55.050 --> 1:46:59.890
<b>在石墙根 有块在缅因州见不到的石头...</b><b>
At the base of that wall, there's a rock that has no earthly business in Maine.</b>

1:47:01.030 --> 1:47:04.050
<b>一块黑色的火山玻璃石</b><b>
Piece of black, volcanic glass.</b>

1:47:06.730 --> 1:47:09.390
<b>下面埋着我给你的东西</b><b>
Something's buried under it I want you to have.</b>

1:47:10.170 --> 1:47:11.340
<b>是什么 安迪?</b><b>
What, Andy?</b>

1:47:11.840 --> 1:47:13.570
<b>那儿埋的是什么?</b><b>
What's buried under there?</b>

1:47:15.170 --> 1:47:16.740
<b>这得你去挖出来...</b><b>
You'll have to pry it up...</b>

1:47:17.240 --> 1:47:18.500
<b>就知道了</b><b>
to see.</b>

1:47:24.380 --> 1:47:26.350
<b>不 我告诉你们 这小子...</b><b>
No, I'm telling you. The guy is...</b>

1:47:27.020 --> 1:47:28.750
<b>他说话时表情怪怪的</b><b>
He's talking funny.</b>

1:47:29.850 --> 1:47:31.460
<b>我真的很担心</b><b>
I'm really worried about him.</b>

1:47:31.960 --> 1:47:33.090
<b>那哥儿几个就上心盯着点</b><b>
Let's keep an eye on him.</b>

1:47:33.590 --> 1:47:36.860
<b>白天没问题 但整晚他都是一个人啊?</b><b>
That's fine during the day, but at night he's all alone.</b>

1:47:38.300 --> 1:47:39.420
<b>哦 我晕死</b><b>
Oh, Lord.</b>

1:47:40.770 --> 1:47:41.600
<b>怎么了?</b><b>
What?</b>

1:47:43.100 --> 1:47:45.570
<b>安迪今天到货场找过我</b><b>
Andy come down to the loading dock today.</b>

1:47:46.070 --> 1:47:47.870
<b>他问我要了根绳子</b><b>
He asked me for a length of rope.</b>

1:47:48.370 --> 1:47:48.910
<b>绳子?</b><b>
Rope?</b>

1:47:49.410 --> 1:47:50.810
<b>六英尺长</b><b>
Six feet long.</b>

1:47:51.310 --> 1:47:52.670
<b>你给他了?</b><b>
And you gave it to him.</b>

1:47:53.550 --> 1:47:55.050
<b>当然 我干嘛不给?</b><b>
Sure. Why wouldn't I?</b>

1:47:55.550 --> 1:47:57.110
<b>天啊! 海伍德!</b><b>
Jesus! Heywood.</b>

1:47:57.720 --> 1:47:59.380
<b>我怎么知道他要干嘛?</b><b>
How was I supposed to know?</b>

1:47:59.880 --> 1:48:00.960
<b>你不记得布鲁克斯了啊?</b><b>
Remember Brooks Hatlen?</b>

1:48:01.460 --> 1:48:05.390
<b>不 安迪不会走那条路的</b><b>
Andy would never do that.</b>

1:48:05.990 --> 1:48:07.050
<b>绝对不会!</b><b>
Never.</b>

1:48:09.130 --> 1:48:10.460
<b>我不知道</b><b>
I don't know.</b>

1:48:13.300 --> 1:48:15.320
<b>人的忍耐是有限度的</b><b>
Every man has his breaking point.</b>

1:48:17.670 --> 1:48:19.740
<b>快点 我得回家了!</b><b>
Lickety-split. Want to get home.</b>

1:48:20.240 --> 1:48:22.000
<b>这就好了 先生!</b><b>
Just about finished, sir.</b>

1:48:39.120 --> 1:48:40.750
<b>今晚有三笔要存!</b><b>
Three deposits tonight.</b>

1:48:48.730 --> 1:48:50.340
<b>把我的衣服送到洗衣房</b><b>
Get my stuff down to the laundry.</b>

1:48:50.840 --> 1:48:52.170
<b>再把我的鞋擦了</b><b>
And shine my shoes.</b>

1:48:52.670 --> 1:48:55.610
<b>要擦得跟镜子一样! 好的 先生</b><b>
- I want them looking like mirrors. - Yes, sir.</b>

1:49:01.110 --> 1:49:02.580
<b>你能回来真好 安迪</b><b>
It's good having you back.</b>

1:49:03.510 --> 1:49:05.380
<b>你不在的时候真是乱套了</b><b>
Place wasn't the same without you.</b>

1:49:52.260 --> 1:49:53.320
<b>熄灯!</b><b>
Lights out!</b>

1:50:26.160 --> 1:50:28.690
<b>记不清我在这里有过多少个难眠之夜</b><b>
I've had some long nights in stir.</b>

1:50:29.230 --> 1:50:31.600
<b>在黑暗中咀嚼孤独 只有一些心事陪着你</b><b>
Alone in the dark with nothing but your thoughts...</b>

1:50:32.100 --> 1:50:34.770
<b>时间被拉长得像刀锋那么细</b><b>
time can draw out like a blade.</b>

1:50:40.110 --> 1:50:43.100
<b>而这一夜则是我一生中最漫长的</b><b>
That was the longest night of my life.</b>

1:50:58.960 --> 1:51:00.120
<b>清点人数!</b><b>
Give me a count!</b>

1:51:04.640 --> 1:51:07.470
<b>南边三楼 到齐!</b><b>
Tier 3 south, clear!</b>

1:51:10.610 --> 1:51:13.480
<b>二楼245人犯未到!</b><b>
Man missing on tier 2, cell 245!</b>

1:51:13.980 --> 1:51:15.040
<b>杜弗瑞恩!</b><b>
Dufresne!</b>

1:51:15.580 --> 1:51:18.010
<b>快出来! 别跟我耍花样!</b><b>
Come out. You're holding up the show!</b>

1:51:21.150 --> 1:51:24.550
<b>别等我过去揪你出来 不然我打爆你的头!</b><b>
Don't make me come down or I'll thump your skull for you!</b>

1:51:32.130 --> 1:51:35.670
<b>你妈的折腾我 我得赶时间做事!</b><b>
Damn it, you're putting me behind! I got a schedule to keep.</b>

1:51:36.170 --> 1:51:39.170
<b>你最好是病了或者死了 否则我让你去吃屎!</b><b>
You'd better be sick or dead in there. I shit you not!</b>

1:51:39.670 --> 1:51:41.000
<b>你听到没有?</b><b>
You hear me?</b>

1:51:47.110 --> 1:51:49.200
<b>哦 我的上帝!</b><b>
Oh, my Holy God.</b>

1:52:06.200 --> 1:52:08.700
<b>查问这个监区的所有人犯</b><b>
I want every man on this cellblock questioned.</b>

1:52:09.200 --> 1:52:13.170
<b>- 从他的朋友开始! - 哪个? - 他!</b><b>
- Start with that friend of his. - Who? - Him!</b>

1:52:14.340 --> 1:52:15.900
<b>打开237号仓门!</b><b>
Open 237.</b>

1:52:19.410 --> 1:52:23.070
<b>你什么意思 "他就是不在这儿了?" 别跟我说这个!</b><b>
What do you mean, "He just wasn't here?" Don't say that to me.</b>

1:52:23.950 --> 1:52:24.980
<b>这话我不想听第二遍!</b><b>
Don't tell me that again.</b>

1:52:25.480 --> 1:52:26.250
<b>但是长官 他是不在了!</b><b>
But sir, he wasn't.</b>

1:52:26.750 --> 1:52:30.210
<b>我看到了! 海格! 你当我瞎的吗?</b><b>
I can see that, Haig! Think I'm blind?</b>

1:52:30.890 --> 1:52:31.990
<b>你的话是不是这意思?</b><b>
Is that what you're saying?</b>

1:52:32.490 --> 1:52:35.150
<b>- 我瞎了吗 海格? - 没有! 长官!</b><b>
- Am I blind, Haig? - No, sir!</b>

1:52:36.060 --> 1:52:38.550
<b>那么你呢? 你瞎的吗?</b><b>
What about you. You blind?</b>

1:52:39.060 --> 1:52:41.330
<b>- 告诉我这是什么? - 昨晚的查房记录!</b><b>
- Tell me what this is. - Last night's count.</b>

1:52:41.830 --> 1:52:44.840
<b>杜弗瑞恩的名字在吗? 我确定在 这儿!</b><b>
You see Dufresne's name there? I sure do. Right there.</b>

1:52:45.340 --> 1:52:46.670
<b>"杜弗瑞恩！"</b><b>
"Dufresne."</b>

1:52:48.340 --> 1:52:50.710
<b>熄灯的时候他还在牢房里</b><b>
He was in his cell...at lights out.</b>

1:52:51.210 --> 1:52:53.470
<b>按道理今早他也应该在牢房里</b><b>
Reasonable he'd be here in the morning.</b>

1:52:54.510 --> 1:52:55.850
<b>马上把他找出来!</b><b>
I want him found.</b>

1:52:56.350 --> 1:52:59.550
<b>不是明天 不是早饭后 就现在!</b><b>
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!</b>

1:53:00.050 --> 1:53:01.250
<b>遵命 长官!</b><b>
Yes, sir.</b>

1:53:02.250 --> 1:53:04.520
<b>跟我来 动作快点!</b><b>
Let's go. Move your butts.</b>

1:53:07.930 --> 1:53:08.910
<b>站好!</b><b>
Stand.</b>

1:53:10.360 --> 1:53:11.420
<b>说吧?</b><b>
Well?</b>

1:53:14.870 --> 1:53:15.570
<b>说什么?</b><b>
Well, what?</b>

1:53:16.070 --> 1:53:19.530
<b>我知道你们俩整天粘在一起 狼狈为奸</b><b>
I see you two all the time. You're thick as thieves, you are.</b>

1:53:20.610 --> 1:53:22.100
<b>他肯定对你说过什么</b><b>
He must have said something.</b>

1:53:22.840 --> 1:53:24.240
<b>没有 长官!</b><b>
No, sir, Warden.</b>

1:53:24.740 --> 1:53:25.710
<b>一个字都没有!</b><b>
Not a word.</b>

1:53:27.550 --> 1:53:30.110
<b>主啊 这是个神迹!</b><b>
Lord, it's a miracle!</b>

1:53:30.720 --> 1:53:33.280
<b>一个大活人像风中放的屁一样没了</b><b>
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.</b>

1:53:33.950 --> 1:53:35.110
<b>整个消失了</b><b>
Nothing left...</b>

1:53:35.950 --> 1:53:38.390
<b>就剩下窗台上几块破石头</b><b>
but some damn rocks on a windowsill.</b>

1:53:38.890 --> 1:53:41.330
<b>还有个墙上的小妞 问问她吧</b><b>
And that cupcake on the wall. Let's ask her.</b>

1:53:41.830 --> 1:53:43.330
<b>也许她知道</b><b>
Maybe she knows.</b>

1:53:43.830 --> 1:53:46.410
<b>你说什么水裤妞儿? 想谈谈吗?</b><b>
What say there, fuzzy-britches? Feel like talking?</b>

1:53:46.910 --> 1:53:49.300
<b>喔 当然不会!</b><b>
Guess not.</b>

1:53:49.870 --> 1:53:52.060
<b>她凭什么知道的多一些?</b><b>
Why should she be any different?</b>

1:53:53.140 --> 1:53:54.800
<b>这是一个阴谋!</b><b>
This is a conspiracy.</b>

1:53:55.440 --> 1:53:57.270
<b>没别的解释!</b><b>
That's what this is.</b>

1:53:57.880 --> 1:54:01.380
<b>一个他妈的大阴谋!</b><b>
One big, damn conspiracy!</b>

1:54:01.880 --> 1:54:03.870
<b>所有人都有份儿!</b><b>
And everyone's in on it!</b>

1:54:04.520 --> 1:54:05.680
<b>包括她!</b><b>
Including her!</b>

1:54:40.720 --> 1:54:42.120
<b>1966年</b><b>
In 1966...</b>

1:54:42.620 --> 1:54:46.780
<b>安迪·杜弗瑞恩从肖申克监狱逃脱</b><b>
Andy Dufresne escaped...from Shawshank Prison.</b>

1:54:49.030 --> 1:54:51.590
<b>他们追查到的只有一套泥泞的囚衣...</b><b>
All they found was a muddy set of prison clothes...</b>

1:54:52.230 --> 1:54:53.470
<b>一块肥皂...</b><b>
a bar of soap...</b>

1:54:53.970 --> 1:54:55.230
<b>还有一把很旧的鹤嘴槌</b><b>
and an old rock hammer...</b>

1:54:55.730 --> 1:54:58.200
<b>槌头几乎要被磨光了</b><b>
damn near worn down to the nub.</b>

1:55:02.710 --> 1:55:07.470
<b>我曾认为用它挖六百年才能挖穿围墙的隧道</b><b>
I had thought it'd take a man 600 years to tunnel through the wall with it.</b>

1:55:08.110 --> 1:55:10.740
<b>安迪只用了不到二十年就办到了</b><b>
Old Andy did it in less than 20.</b>

1:55:29.030 --> 1:55:31.330
<b>安迪热爱地质学</b><b>
Oh, Andy loved geology.</b>

1:55:32.100 --> 1:55:35.170
<b>我肯定这源自于他一丝不苟的性格</b><b>
I imagine it appealed to his meticulous nature.</b>

1:55:35.670 --> 1:55:40.430
<b>正如曾经的冰河时期造就了千百万年的山脉一般</b><b>
An ice age here...million years of mountain building there.</b>

1:55:41.450 --> 1:55:44.020
<b>地质学是关于压力和时间的研究</b><b>
Geology is the study of pressure and time.</b>

1:55:44.520 --> 1:55:47.110
<b>而这也正是他面临的全部问题</b><b>
That's all it takes, really.</b>

1:55:47.850 --> 1:55:48.940
<b>压力...</b><b>
Pressure...</b>

1:55:49.590 --> 1:55:50.850
<b>和时间...</b><b>
and time.</b>

1:55:52.190 --> 1:55:54.250
<b>当然还有一张大海报</b><b>
That and a big goddamn poster.</b>

1:55:58.300 --> 1:55:59.230
<b>就像我所说的</b><b>
Like I said...</b>

1:55:59.730 --> 1:56:03.720
<b>在监狱里 每个人都会找些事情把脑子塞满</b><b>
in prison, a man will do anything to keep his mind occupied.</b>

1:56:06.540 --> 1:56:11.340
<b>看来安迪最喜欢的是把他的墙壁搬运到操场上</b><b>
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting his wall out into the exercise yard...</b>

1:56:11.880 --> 1:56:13.810
<b>一次满满两把</b><b>
a handful at a time.</b>

1:56:15.110 --> 1:56:16.880
<b>我估计汤米被杀后</b><b>
I guess after Tommy was killed...</b>

1:56:17.380 --> 1:56:20.050
<b>安迪认定他在这儿已经呆够了</b><b>
Andy decided he'd been here long enough.</b>

1:56:20.550 --> 1:56:23.110
<b>快点 我得回家了!</b><b>
Lickety-split. I want to get home.</b>

1:56:23.850 --> 1:56:25.880
<b>这就好了 先生!</b><b>
I'm just about finished, sir.</b>

1:56:47.340 --> 1:56:49.280
<b>今晚有三笔要存!</b><b>
Three deposits tonight.</b>

1:56:56.590 --> 1:56:58.590
<b>安迪按照吩咐</b><b>
Andy did like he was told.</b>

1:56:59.090 --> 1:57:02.580
<b>把鞋擦得闪闪发亮</b><b>
Buffed those shoes to a high mirror-shine.</b>

1:57:06.260 --> 1:57:08.370
<b>守卫完全没有注意到</b><b>
The guards simply didn't notice.</b>

1:57:08.870 --> 1:57:10.030
<b>我也没有</b><b>
Neither did I.</b>

1:57:10.530 --> 1:57:11.770
<b>说认真的</b><b>
I mean, seriously...</b>

1:57:12.270 --> 1:57:15.260
<b>谁会没事干去盯别人穿什么鞋子呢?</b><b>
how often do you really look at a man's shoes?</b>

1:59:18.830 --> 1:59:21.730
<b>安迪爬向自由 穿过恶臭满盈的五百码</b><b>
Andy crawled to freedom through 500 yards...</b>

1:59:22.230 --> 1:59:25.570
<b>我简直想都不敢想那有多臭</b><b>
of shit-smelling foulness I can't even imagine.</b>

1:59:26.570 --> 1:59:28.900
<b>或许我只是不愿去想</b><b>
Or maybe I just don't want to.</b>

1:59:33.310 --> 1:59:35.680
<b>五百码</b><b>
Five hundred yards.</b>

1:59:36.180 --> 1:59:39.240
<b>有五个橄榄球场那么长</b><b>
That's the length of five football fields.</b>

1:59:39.880 --> 1:59:42.440
<b>差不多有半英里</b><b>
Just shy of half a mile.</b>

2:00:37.680 --> 2:00:42.080
<b>第二天早上 就在拉蔻儿的小秘密被揭穿的同时</b><b>
The next morning, right about the time Raquel was spilling her secret...</b>

2:00:42.580 --> 2:00:45.150
<b>一位与任何人都素昧平生的男子</b><b>
a man nobody ever laid eyes on before...</b>

2:00:45.650 --> 2:00:48.240
<b>来到缅因州国家银行</b><b>
strolled into the Maine National Bank.</b>

2:00:48.820 --> 2:00:51.980
<b>在此之前 他一直活在文件中</b><b>
Until that moment, he didn't exist.</b>

2:00:52.560 --> 2:00:54.830
<b>我可以帮您吗?</b><b>
- Except on paper. - May I help you?</b>

2:00:55.330 --> 2:00:56.960
<b>他持有所有正确的身份证明文件...</b><b>
He had all the proper ID...</b>

2:00:57.460 --> 2:01:01.100
<b>驾驶执照、出生证明、社保卡...</b><b>
driver's license, birth certificate, Social Security card...</b>

2:01:01.600 --> 2:01:03.840
<b>签名也完全吻合</b><b>
And the signature was a spot-on match.</b>

2:01:04.340 --> 2:01:07.140
<b>非常遗憾失去您这样一位好客户</b><b>
I must say I'm sorry to be losing your business.</b>

2:01:07.640 --> 2:01:09.370
<b>希望你在国外生活愉快!</b><b>
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.</b>

2:01:10.170 --> 2:01:11.270
<b>谢谢!</b><b>
Thank you.</b>

2:01:11.940 --> 2:01:13.100
<b>我想我会的!</b><b>
I'm sure I will.</b>

2:01:14.010 --> 2:01:17.050
<b>先生 这是你的本票 还有什么能帮您的吗?</b><b>
Here's your cashier's check, sir. Will there be anything else?</b>

2:01:17.550 --> 2:01:18.540
<b>请问</b><b>
Please.</b>

2:01:19.120 --> 2:01:21.610
<b>能帮我把它寄出去吗?</b><b>
Would you add this to your outgoing mail?</b>

2:01:22.120 --> 2:01:23.310
<b>很高兴为您服务!</b><b>
I'd be happy to.</b>

2:01:25.120 --> 2:01:26.450
<b>- 再见! - 走好 先生!</b><b>
Good day, sir.</b>

2:01:27.390 --> 2:01:31.800
<b>史蒂文先生那天早上走访了波特兰地区近十二家银行</b><b>
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks in the Portland area that morning.</b>

2:01:32.300 --> 2:01:33.600
<b>全部算起来</b><b>
All told, he blew town...</b>

2:01:34.100 --> 2:01:38.930
<b>他让典狱长诺顿的三十七万多美元灰飞烟灭</b><b>
with better than $370,000 of Warden Norton's money.</b>

2:01:39.640 --> 2:01:42.400
<b>十九年刑期的遣散费</b><b>
Severance pay for 19 years.</b>

2:01:49.650 --> 2:01:51.530
<b>早上好 波特兰号角报!</b><b>
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.</b>

2:01:52.030 --> 2:01:56.460
<b>肖申克的贪污与谋杀 检察官掌握黑钱证据 检控指日可待</b>

2:02:02.870 --> 2:02:04.740
<b>主的审判将会迅速降临</b>

2:02:18.060 --> 2:02:19.190
<b>《圣经》</b>

2:02:21.860 --> 2:02:26.190
<b>亲爱的典狱长 你说的没错 得救之道 就在其中</b>

2:02:28.530 --> 2:02:30.020
<b>出埃及记</b>

2:02:43.910 --> 2:02:46.610
<b>拜伦·哈德利? 你有权保持沉默</b><b>
Byron Hadley? You have the right to remain silent.</b>

2:02:47.110 --> 2:02:52.280
<b>否则你所说的一切都将成为呈堂证供</b><b>
If you give up this right, anything you say can be held against you in court.</b>

2:02:52.780 --> 2:02:55.860
<b>我没有亲眼看到 但我听说拜伦·哈德利</b><b>
I wasn't there to see, but I hear Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...</b>

2:02:56.360 --> 2:02:58.940
<b>被带走时哭得像个小女生</b><b>
when they took him away.</b>

2:03:04.130 --> 2:03:08.220
<b>诺顿不愿简单俯首就擒</b><b>
Norton had no intention of going that quietly.</b>

2:03:24.070 --> 2:03:24.900
<b>山姆·诺顿?</b><b>
Samuel Norton.</b>

2:03:25.710 --> 2:03:28.140
<b>我们有你的拘捕令 开门!</b><b>
We have a warrant for your arrest. Open up.</b>

2:03:32.880 --> 2:03:33.980
<b>把门打开!</b><b>
Open the door.</b>

2:03:34.520 --> 2:03:35.780
<b>我不知道是哪把钥匙</b><b>
I'm not sure which key.</b>

2:03:45.930 --> 2:03:47.860
<b>请你配合 诺顿!</b><b>
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!</b>

2:03:59.380 --> 2:04:02.550
<b>我相信最后时刻经过他大脑的</b><b>
I like to think the last thing that went through his head...</b>

2:04:03.050 --> 2:04:04.350
<b>除了一颗子弹</b><b>
other than that bullet...</b>

2:04:04.850 --> 2:04:09.290
<b>一定还有对栽在安迪手里的难以置信和迷惑不解</b><b>
was to wonder how the hell Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.</b>

2:04:11.790 --> 2:04:15.030
<b>诺顿一伙倒台不久</b><b>
Not long after the warden deprived us of his company...</b>

2:04:15.530 --> 2:04:17.590
<b>我收到一张明信片</b><b>
I got a postcard in the mail.</b>

2:04:19.060 --> 2:04:21.600
<b>什么都没写 邮戳是...</b><b>
It was blank, but the postmark said...</b>

2:04:22.100 --> 2:04:24.230
<b>汉考克口岸 德克萨斯</b><b>
Fort Hancock, Texas.</b>

2:04:24.770 --> 2:04:25.900
<b>汉考克口岸</b><b>
Fort Hancock...</b>

2:04:26.400 --> 2:04:28.040
<b>就在边境线上</b><b>
right on the border.</b>

2:04:28.540 --> 2:04:29.820
<b>那是安迪出境的地方</b><b>
That's where Andy crossed.</b>

2:04:30.320 --> 2:04:35.080
<b>每当我脑海中浮现他驾着敞篷车一路向南的画面时</b><b>
When I picture him heading south in his own car with the top down...</b>

2:04:35.580 --> 2:04:37.810
<b>我总会忍不住笑出来</b><b>
it always makes me laugh.</b>

2:04:39.650 --> 2:04:41.090
<b>安迪·杜弗瑞恩</b><b>
Andy Dufresne...</b>

2:04:41.590 --> 2:04:43.320
<b>爬过了臭水沟</b><b>
who crawled through a river of shit...</b>

2:04:43.820 --> 2:04:46.220
<b>洗清了罪孽 在彼岸重生</b><b>
and came out clean on the other side.</b>

2:04:47.060 --> 2:04:48.420
<b>安迪·杜弗瑞恩</b><b>
Andy Dufresne...</b>

2:04:49.230 --> 2:04:50.820
<b>直奔太平洋而去</b><b>
headed for the Pacific.</b>

2:04:53.800 --> 2:04:55.670
<b>哈德利撕住他的领口 对吗?</b><b>
Hadley's got him by the throat, right?</b>

2:04:56.170 --> 2:04:59.670
<b>他说 "这鸟人想给自己来一出意外"</b><b>
He says, " I believe this boy's about to have himself an accident."</b>

2:05:00.170 --> 2:05:03.040
<b>我们几个跟他最熟的时常聊起他</b><b>
Those of us who knew him best talk about him often.</b>

2:05:03.710 --> 2:05:05.110
<b>我发誓 他有种神奇的魅力</b><b>
I swear, the stuff he pulled...</b>

2:05:05.610 --> 2:05:08.410
<b>"我的朋友能有几瓶啤酒"</b><b>
"My friends could use a couple of beers."</b>

2:05:08.910 --> 2:05:10.570
<b>他办到了!</b><b>
And he got it!</b>

2:05:11.820 --> 2:05:15.920
<b>有时我会伤感 因为安迪已经不在了</b><b>
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...Andy being gone.</b>

2:05:16.620 --> 2:05:20.720
<b>我只能提醒自己有些鸟是不能关在笼子里的</b><b>
I have to remind myself that some birds aren't meant to be caged.</b>

2:05:21.220 --> 2:05:23.280
<b>它们的羽翼是如此绚丽 光芒夺目</b><b>
Their feathers are just too bright.</b>

2:05:25.000 --> 2:05:25.970
<b>当它们飞出牢笼时</b><b>
And when they fly away...</b>

2:05:26.470 --> 2:05:31.570
<b>会让那些觉得把它们关起来是种罪恶的人感到由衷的喜悦</b><b>
the part of you that knows it was a sin to lock them up does rejoice.</b>

2:05:32.640 --> 2:05:38.710
<b>但同时 它们的离开让你生活的地方空荡荡的</b><b>
But still...the place you live in is that much more drab and empty that they're gone.</b>

2:05:42.910 --> 2:05:45.280
<b>可能我只是过于想念我的朋友了</b><b>
I guess I just miss my friend.</b>

2:06:09.970 --> 2:06:10.910
<b>请坐!</b><b>
Please sit down.</b>

2:06:16.750 --> 2:06:18.310
<b>艾力斯·博伊德·瑞丁（瑞德的全名）</b><b>
Ellis Boyd Redding...</b>

2:06:18.850 --> 2:06:22.110
<b>你因终身监禁已被关了40年了</b><b>
your files say you've served 40 years of a life sentence.</b>

2:06:22.920 --> 2:06:25.050
<b>你觉得你改过自新了吗?</b><b>
You feel you've been rehabilitated?</b>

2:06:26.920 --> 2:06:28.480
<b>改过自新?</b><b>
Rehabilitated?</b>

2:06:30.530 --> 2:06:32.430
<b>哦 让我想想看</b><b>
Well, now, let me see.</b>

2:06:33.430 --> 2:06:35.760
<b>我不明白那是什么意思</b><b>
I don't have any idea what that means.</b>

2:06:37.870 --> 2:06:40.130
<b>意思是你已经准备好重返社会...</b><b>
It means you're ready to rejoin society...</b>

2:06:40.700 --> 2:06:43.040
<b>我知道你是怎么想的 老弟</b><b>
I know what you think it means, sonny.</b>

2:06:45.210 --> 2:06:47.200
<b>对我来说那只是一个构词法的产物</b><b>
To me it's just a made-up word.</b>

2:06:48.550 --> 2:06:50.810
<b>给政客们用的词汇</b><b>
A politician's word so that...</b>

2:06:51.310 --> 2:06:54.820
<b>让你这样的年轻人能穿西装打领带</b><b>
young fellas like yourself can wear a suit and a tie...</b>

2:06:55.320 --> 2:06:56.910
<b>有事可做</b><b>
and have a job.</b>

2:06:58.890 --> 2:07:00.980
<b>你倒底想知道些什么?</b><b>
What do you really want to know?</b>

2:07:01.760 --> 2:07:03.070
<b>我对自己的罪行感到后悔吗?</b><b>
Am I sorry for what I did?</b>

2:07:03.570 --> 2:07:05.320
<b>那么 你后悔吗?</b><b>
Well, are you?</b>

2:07:06.640 --> 2:07:10.060
<b>没有一天我不感到后悔的</b><b>
There's not a day goes by I don't feel regret.</b>

2:07:10.840 --> 2:07:14.890
<b>不是因为我被关在这儿 或者为了迎合你的想法</b><b>
Not because I'm in here or because you think I should.</b>

2:07:17.780 --> 2:07:20.940
<b>我回首往事</b><b>
I look back on the way I was then...</b>

2:07:22.490 --> 2:07:28.840
<b>一个年轻的...愚蠢的孩子铸成大错</b><b>
a young...stupid kid who committed that terrible crime.</b>

2:07:31.260 --> 2:07:33.550
<b>我想和他谈谈</b><b>
I want to talk to him.</b>

2:07:34.900 --> 2:07:37.600
<b>想和他讲讲人生大义</b><b>
I want to try and talk some sense to him.</b>

2:07:38.100 --> 2:07:40.630
<b>教教他为人处世之道</b><b>
Tell him the way things are.</b>

2:07:42.140 --> 2:07:44.170
<b>但我做不到</b><b>
But I can't.</b>

2:07:45.780 --> 2:07:48.360
<b>那孩子早都不在了</b><b>
That kid's long gone...</b>

2:07:48.980 --> 2:07:52.340
<b>只剩下你面前这个老头子</b><b>
and this old man is all that's left.</b>

2:07:53.150 --> 2:07:55.210
<b>我得跟他继续生活</b><b>
I got to live with that.</b>

2:07:55.990 --> 2:07:57.560
<b>改过自新?</b><b>
Rehabilitated?</b>

2:07:58.060 --> 2:08:00.330
<b>只是个狗屁字眼</b><b>
It's just a bullshit word.</b>

2:08:00.830 --> 2:08:06.190
<b>请你继续 在表格上盖章吧 老弟 别浪费我的时间了</b><b>
So you go on and stamp your forms, sonny, and stop wasting my time.</b>

2:08:07.420 --> 2:08:09.530
<b>说句实话</b><b>
Because to tell you the truth...</b>

2:08:10.030 --> 2:08:12.020
<b>我根本不在乎!</b><b>
I don't give a shit.</b>

2:08:25.330 --> 2:08:25.830
<b>批准</b>

2:09:37.960 --> 2:09:39.950
<b>你的 小姐</b><b>
Here you go, miss.</b>

2:09:42.300 --> 2:09:43.910
<b>可以去趟洗手间吗?</b><b>
Restroom break?</b>

2:09:49.140 --> 2:09:54.250
<b>你不用每次要小便都来问我 只管去就是了!</b><b>
You don't need to ask me every time you need to go take a piss. Just go.</b>

2:10:06.720 --> 2:10:10.120
<b>四十年来我连小便都需要被批准</b><b>
Forty years I've been asking permission to piss.</b>

2:10:10.620 --> 2:10:14.210
<b>不申请的话一滴都挤不出来</b><b>
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.</b>

2:10:17.130 --> 2:10:19.880
<b>现实是很难面对的</b><b>
There's a harsh truth to face.</b>

2:10:20.970 --> 2:10:24.460
<b>我没办法习惯外面的生活</b><b>
No way I'm going to make it on the outside.</b>

2:10:31.740 --> 2:10:35.750
<b>我总在想怎样才能违反假释条例</b><b>
All I do anymore is think of ways to break my parole...</b>

2:10:36.250 --> 2:10:39.310
<b>那样他们会把我送回去</b><b>
so maybe they'd send me back.</b>

2:10:43.920 --> 2:10:46.760
<b>生活在恐惧中是很可怕的事</b><b>
Terrible thing, to live in fear.</b>

2:10:47.260 --> 2:10:48.630
<b>布鲁克斯知道</b><b>
Brooks Hatlen knew it.</b>

2:10:49.130 --> 2:10:51.650
<b>他知道得太清楚了</b><b>
Knew it all too well.</b>

2:10:52.660 --> 2:10:56.000
<b>我只想回到适合我的地方</b><b>
All I want is to be back where things make sense.</b>

2:10:56.500 --> 2:10:59.820
<b>不用惶惶不可终日的地方</b><b>
Where I won't have to be afraid all the time.</b>

2:11:01.240 --> 2:11:04.200
<b>只是有一件事阻止了我</b><b>
Only one thing stops me.</b>

2:11:05.040 --> 2:11:08.040
<b>我答应安迪的事</b><b>
A promise I made to Andy.</b>

2:11:27.970 --> 2:11:29.680
<b>到了!</b><b>
There it is.</b>

2:11:39.710 --> 2:11:41.960
<b>非常感谢 先生!</b><b>
Much obliged, sir.</b>

2:15:20.700 --> 2:15:21.700
<b>亲爱的瑞德</b><b>
Dear Red:</b>

2:15:22.200 --> 2:15:24.370
<b>若你能看到这封信 那你已经出来了</b><b>
If you're reading this, you've gotten out...</b>

2:15:24.870 --> 2:15:28.710
<b>既然你已经跑了这么远 不妨再跑远一点</b><b>
and if you've come this far, maybe you'd come a bit further.</b>

2:15:29.210 --> 2:15:32.270
<b>你还记得那个地方的名字 是吗?</b><b>
You remember the name of the town, don't you?</b>

2:15:33.980 --> 2:15:36.060
<b>芝华塔尼欧!</b><b>
Zihuatanejo!</b>

2:15:37.120 --> 2:15:40.720
<b>我需要一个能干的人和我一起完成我的计划</b><b>
I could use a good man to help me get my project on wheels.</b>

2:15:41.220 --> 2:15:45.060
<b>我期待你的到来 棋盘已经准备好了</b><b>
I'll keep an eye out for you, and the chessboard ready.</b>

2:15:45.560 --> 2:15:46.790
<b>记住 瑞德</b><b>
Remember, Red...</b>

2:15:47.290 --> 2:15:49.100
<b>希望是个好东西</b><b>
hope is a good thing...</b>

2:15:49.600 --> 2:15:51.300
<b>也许是世间最好的东西</b><b>
maybe the best of things.</b>

2:15:51.800 --> 2:15:54.000
<b>好东西从不会逝去</b><b>
And no good thing ever dies.</b>

2:15:54.500 --> 2:15:57.070
<b>我希望这封信能等到你</b><b>
I will be hoping that this letter finds you...</b>

2:15:57.570 --> 2:15:59.310
<b>并能看到你安然无恙</b><b>
and finds you well.</b>

2:15:59.810 --> 2:16:00.740
<b>你的朋友</b><b>
Your friend...</b>

2:16:01.240 --> 2:16:02.990
<b>安迪</b><b>
Andy.</b>

2:16:36.240 --> 2:16:37.680
<b>"要么忙着活</b><b>
"Get busy living...</b>

2:16:38.180 --> 2:16:40.670
<b>要么忙着死"</b><b>
or get busy dying. "</b>

2:16:42.780 --> 2:16:45.530
<b>这话太他妈的对了</b><b>
That's goddamn right.</b>

2:16:47.620 --> 2:16:49.420
<b>瑞德也住过</b>

2:16:50.190 --> 2:16:52.060
<b>这是有生以来第二次...</b><b>
For the second time in my life...</b>

2:16:52.560 --> 2:16:55.700
<b>我有做贼心虚的感觉</b><b>
I'm guilty of committing a crime.</b>

2:16:56.200 --> 2:17:02.630
<b>我担心他们会设下路障 当然 这是因为有人违反假释条例</b><b>
Parole violation. Of course I doubt they'll toss up any roadblocks for that.</b>

2:17:03.130 --> 2:17:04.870
<b>而不是为了我这种老家伙</b><b>
Not for an old crook like me.</b>

2:17:05.370 --> 2:17:07.990
<b>德克萨斯州 汉考克口岸 谢谢!</b><b>
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.</b>

2:17:11.080 --> 2:17:15.750
<b>我发现我很兴奋 如坐针毡 思绪纷乱</b><b>
I find I'm so excited I can barely sit still or hold a thought in my head.</b>

2:17:16.250 --> 2:17:19.290
<b>我想这是一个自由人才能感受到的兴奋</b><b>
I think it's the excitement only a free man can feel.</b>

2:17:19.790 --> 2:17:21.990
<b>一个自由人开始了漫长的旅程</b><b>
A free man at the start of a long journey...</b>

2:17:22.490 --> 2:17:25.670
<b>伴随着未知的结局</b><b>
whose conclusion is uncertain.</b>

2:17:28.090 --> 2:17:31.350
<b>我希望我能越过边界 完成这段旅程</b><b>
I hope I can make it across the border.</b>

2:17:32.260 --> 2:17:35.880
<b>我希望见到我的朋友 紧握他的手</b><b>
I hope to see my friend and shake his hand.</b>

2:17:37.170 --> 2:17:41.820
<b>我希望太平洋的海水和我梦中一样蓝</b><b>
I hope the Pacific is as blue as it has been in my dreams.</b>

2:17:43.160 --> 2:17:44.860
<b>我希望...</b><b>
I hope.</b>

